# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:24
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "引言"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:24
msgid ""
"The primary goals of these Release Notes are to inform users of major "
"changes in this release of the Debian distribution, to provide information "
"on how to upgrade safely from the previous to the this release and finally "
"to inform users of known potential issues users could encounter when "
"upgrading to or using the release."
msgstr "这些发行注记的主要目的是用来让用户知道在这个 Debian 发行版本中的主要变化，"
"提供一些如何方能平稳得由旧有版本升级至本发行版本的信息，"
"并在文末提供给用户一些在升级或使用本发行版本时可能会遭遇到的已知问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:24
msgid ""
"Note that it is impossible to list every known issue and that therefore a "
"selection has been made based on a combination of the expected prevalence "
"and impact of issues."
msgstr "请注意到，要列出所有的已知问题是不可能的。"
"因此，这些都是在经过筛选之后，被认为是普遍存在且重大的问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:24
msgid ""
"The most recent version of this document is always available at <url id="
"\"&url-release-notes;\">. If your version is more than a month old, you "
"might wish to download the latest version."
msgstr "这份文件的最新版本可于 <url id=\"&url-release-notes;\"> 取得。如果在您手上的"
"已经是一个月以前的版本的话，您可能就要考虑下载新的版本了。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:24
msgid ""
"Please note that we only support and document upgrading from the previous "
"release of Debian (in this case, the upgrade from &oldreleasename;). If you "
"need to upgrade from older releases, we suggest you read previous editions "
"of the release notes."
msgstr "请注意到，在此只会提供及记述从上一个 Debian 发行版本进行升级的信息。"
"（也就是说，由 &oldreleasename; 进行升级）。"
"如果您必须从更为早期的发行版进行升级的话，我们建议您能参阅旧有的发行注记。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:61
msgid "What's new in &debian; &release;"
msgstr "在 &debian; &release; 中有什么新增功能"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:61
msgid ""
"This release adds official support for the AMD64 architecture which supports "
"64-bit processors from both Intel (EM64T) and AMD (AMD64). During the "
"previous release, &debian; 3.1 ('sarge'), an unofficial version of this port "
"was available. Upgrading from this unofficial version should be possible "
"using these Release Notes, but is not supported."
msgstr "在这个发行版中新增了对 AMD64 平台的官方支持，也就是支持了由 Intel (EM64T) 及 AMD (AMD64) 所提供 64 位的处理器。"
"在上一个发行版 &debian; 3.1 ('sarge') 中则仅对此提供了非官方版本。"
"由这个发行注记来从这个非官方版本进行升级是可行的，但并不支持。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:61
msgid ""
"Official support for the Motorola 680x0 ('m68k') architecture has been "
"dropped because it did not meet the criteria set by the Debian Release "
"Managers. The most important underlying reasons are performance and limited "
"upstream support for essential toolchain components. However, the m68k port "
"is expected to remain active and available for installation even if not a "
"part of this official stable release."
msgstr "对于 Motorola 680x0 ('m68k') 平台的官方支持已经停止，"
"因为它无法达到 Debian Release Managers 所设置的标准。"
"而最根本的潜在原因是一些基本工具元件的效能及极为有限的原厂支持。"
"然而，即使它无法列入官方稳定发行版，"
"m68k 平台移植还是会继续存在且可取得以进行安装。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:61
msgid ""
"The following are the officially supported architectures for &debian; "
"&releasename;:"
msgstr "以下是 &debian; &releasename; 官方所支持的硬件平台："

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "Intel x86 ('i386')"
msgstr "Intel x86 ('i386')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "Alpha ('alpha')"
msgstr "Alpha ('alpha')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "SPARC ('sparc')"
msgstr "SPARC ('sparc')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "PowerPC ('powerpc')"
msgstr "PowerPC ('powerpc')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "ARM ('arm')"
msgstr "ARM ('arm')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "MIPS ('mips' (Big endian) and 'mipsel' (Little endian))"
msgstr "MIPS ('mips' (Big endian) 及 'mipsel' (Little endian))"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "Intel Itanium ('ia64')"
msgstr "Intel Itanium ('ia64')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "HP PA-RISC ('hppa')"
msgstr "HP PA-RISC ('hppa')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "S/390 ('s390')"
msgstr "S/390 ('s390')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:85
msgid "AMD64 ('amd64')"
msgstr "AMD64 ('amd64')"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:100
msgid ""
"You can read more about port status, and port-specific information for your "
"architecture at the <url id=\"&url-ports;\" name=\"Debian port web pages\">."
msgstr "您可以在 <url id=\"&url-ports;\" name=\"Debian 硬件结构网页\"> 中取得更多关于"
"各个平台移植的情况，以及针对移植至您的硬件平台的相关信息。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:100
msgid ""
"This is only the second official release of &debian; for the &arch-title; "
"architecture. We feel that it has proven itself sufficiently to be released. "
"However, because it has not had the exposure (and hence testing by users) "
"that our releases on other architectures have had, you may encounter a few "
"bugs. Please use our <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name=\"bug tracking system\"> to "
"report any problems; make sure to mention the fact that the bug is on the "
"&architecture; platform."
msgstr "虽然这仅仅是 &debian; 在 &arch-title; 平台上的第二次正式发行，但我们觉得系统"
"本身已经证明了它已达到了可公开发行的水平。然而，因为它从来没有像其他平台上的"
"发行版那么的知名，那么的能被用户大量测试，所以您还是可能会遭遇到一些问题。"
"请利用我们的 <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name=\"错误跟踪系统\"> 来回报您所发现的任"
"何问题；在报告中请不要忘了提及您是在 &architecture; 平台上发现这个错误的。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:100
msgid ""
"&debian; &release; for the &arch-title; architecture ships with kernel "
"version &kernelversion;."
msgstr "在 &arch-title; 平台上的 &debian; &release; 发行版所使用的内核版本为 "
"&kernelversion;。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:100
msgid "What's new in the distribution?"
msgstr "在这次的发行版本中有什么新变化？"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:120
msgid ""
"This new release of Debian again comes with a lot more software than its "
"predecessor &oldreleasename;; the distribution includes over 6200 new "
"packages. Most of the software in the distribution has been updated: over "
"10500 software packages (this is 67% of all packages in &oldreleasename;). "
"Also, a significant number of packages (over 3400, 22% of the packages in "
"&oldreleasename;) have for various reasons been removed from the "
"distribution. You will not see any updates for these packages and they will "
"be marked as 'obsolete' in package management front-ends."
msgstr "比起之前的 &oldreleasename;，新的 Debian 发行版再度收集了更多的软件；"
"在这次的发行版本里包含了超过 6200 个新软件包，且大部份的软件都被更新了（接近 10500 个软"
"件包，大约占了 &oldreleasename; 的软件包数量的 67%）。"
"当然啰，因为种种的原因，也有不少的软件（超过 3400 个"
"，大约占了 &oldreleasename; 的软件包数量的 22%）在这次的发行版本里被"
"移除掉了。您会发觉到这些软件包的版本已不再更新，并且在软件包的管理界面里它们会被标"
"记为 '废弃(obsolete)' 软件包。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:120
msgid ""
"With this release &debian; switches from XFree86 to the 7.1 release of X."
"Org, which includes support for a greater range of hardware and better "
"autodetection. This allows the use of Compiz, which is one of the first "
"compositing window managers for the X Window System, taking full advantage "
"of hardware OpenGL-acceleration for supported devices."
msgstr "从 &debian; 这个发行版本开始，已由 XFree86 转换为支持了更多的硬件及更佳的自动探测的 X.Org 7.1 版了。"
"它可以使用 Compiz 这个第一个能够在被支持的设备上充份利用硬件 OpenGL 加速的 X Window System 复合式窗口管理程序。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:120
msgid ""
"&debian; again ships with several desktop applications and environments. "
"Amongst others it now includes the desktop environments GNOME "
"2.14<footnote>With some modules from GNOME 2.16</footnote>, KDE 3.5.5a, and "
"Xfce 4.4. Productivity applications have also been upgraded, including the "
"office suites OpenOffice.org 2.0.4a and KOffice 1.6 as well as GNUcash "
"2.0.5, GNUmeric 1.6.3 and Abiword 2.4.6"
msgstr "&debian; 再次搭载了众多的桌面应用软件及桌面环境。"
"其中，像是包含了<footnote>采用一些来自 GNOME 2.16 的模块</footnote>的桌面环境 GNOME 2.14、"
"KDE 3.5.5a 及 Xfce 4.4。还有一些能提升工作效率的软件，包含办公室套件 OpenOffice.org 2.0.4a 及 KOffice 1.6 和 GNUcash "
"2.0.5、GNUmeric 1.6.3 及 Abiword 2.4.6。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:120
msgid ""
"Updates to other desktop applications include the upgrade of Evolution 2.6.3 "
"and Gaim 2.0. The Mozilla suite has also been updated but the main programs "
"have been renamed: <prgn>iceweasel</prgn> (version 2.0.0.2) is the unbranded "
"<prgn>Firefox</prgn> web browser and <prgn>icedove</prgn> (version 1.5) is "
"the unbranded <prgn>Thunderbird</prgn> mail client."
msgstr "其它的桌面应用程序也被更新了，包含了更新为 Evolution 2.6.3 及 Gaim 2.0。"
"Mozilla 组合也被更新了，但主要程序已更名：<prgn>iceweasel</prgn>（2.0.0.2 版）是无商标的 "
"<prgn>Firefox</prgn> 网页浏览器，<prgn>icedove</prgn>（1.5 版）则为"
"无商标的 <prgn>Thunderbird</prgn> 邮件客户端。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:120
msgid ""
"This release also includes, amongst others, the following software updates:"
msgstr "在此发行版中也包含了以下的软件更新"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:153
msgid "the GNU C library, version 2.3.6."
msgstr "GNU C 函数库，2.3.6 版。"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:153
msgid "the GNU Compiler Collection 4.1 as default compiler."
msgstr "将 GNU Compiler Collection 4.1 做为默认的编译器。"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:153
msgid "Language interpreters: PHP 5.5, Python 2.4."
msgstr "直译语言：PHP 5.5、Python 2.4。"

# type: <item><p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:153
msgid "Server software:"
msgstr "服务器软件："

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:163
msgid ""
"e-mail servers: Exim 4.63 (default email server for new installations), "
"Postfix 2.3, Courier 0.53, Cyrus 2.2."
msgstr "电子邮件服务器：Exim 4.63（将是新安装系统默认的电子邮件服务器）、Postfix 2.3、Courier 0.53、Cyrus 2.2。"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:168
msgid "web servers: Apache 2.2, fnord 1.10"
msgstr "Web 服务器：Apache 2.2、fnord 1.10"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:168
msgid "database servers: MySQL 5.0.32, PostgreSQL 8.1"
msgstr "数据库服务器：MySQL 5.0.32、PostgreSQL 8.1"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:168
msgid "the OpenSSH server, version 4.3."
msgstr "OpenSSH 服务器，4.3 版。"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:168
msgid "name servers: Bind 9.3, maradns 1.2."
msgstr "名称服务器：Bind 9.3、maradns 1.2。"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:168
msgid "directory server: OpenLDAP 2.3"
msgstr "目录服务器：OpenLDAP 2.3"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:179
msgid ""
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn> is the preferred program for package management from "
"console. <prgn>aptitude</prgn> supports most command line operations of "
"<prgn>apt-get</prgn> and has proven to be better at dependency resolution "
"than <prgn>apt-get</prgn>. If you are still using <prgn>dselect</prgn>, you "
"should switch to <package>aptitude</package> as the official frontend for "
"package management."
msgstr "<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 是在控制台 (Console) 上的软件包管理程序的第一选择。"
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 支持了大部份的 <prgn>apt-get</prgn> 在命令行上的操作口令，"
"且在处理依赖问题上，已证实它的表现优于 <prgn>apt-get</prgn>。"
"如果您还在使用 <prgn>dselect</prgn>，您应该将软件包管理时的官方前端界面转换为使用 <package>aptitude</package>。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:179
msgid ""
"The official &debian; distribution now ships on thirteen to fifteen binary "
"CDs (depending on the architecture) and a similar number of source CDs. A "
"DVD version of the distribution is also available."
msgstr "官方的 &debian; 发行版包含了十三至十五张（视系统架构而定）的程序光盘及数量相"
"当的源码光盘，同时 DVD 发行版也已经推出。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:196
msgid "Secure APT"
msgstr "安全的 APT"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:200
msgid ""
"<prgn>apt-secure</prgn> (also known as <em>Secure APT</em> is now available "
"in &releasename;. This feature adds extra security to &debian; systems by "
"easily supporting strong cryptography and digital signatures to validate "
"downloaded packages. This release includes the <prgn>apt-key</prgn> tool for "
"adding new keys to apt's keyring, which by default includes only the current "
"Debian archive signing key, provided in the <package>debian-archive-keyring</"
"package>."
msgstr "在 &releasename; 中现已提供了 <prgn>apt-secure</prgn>（也称作 <em>Secure APT</em>）。"
"这个功能能够轻易得支持强力的验证码及数位签章以用来检验下载到的软件包，让 &debian; 系统能得到更进一步的保障。"
"这个发行版本中还包含了 <prgn>apt-key</prgn> 工具以便能将新的金钥加入 apt 的金钥库中。"
"它默认上只收录了由 <package>debian-archive-keyring</package> 所提供的，当前的 Debian 档案库的签名金钥。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:200
msgid ""
"In its default configuration, <prgn>apt-secure</prgn> will warn if packages "
"are downloaded from sources that are not authenticated. Future releases "
"might force all packages to be verified before downloading them. Unofficial "
"apt sources administrators are encouraged to generate a cryptographic key "
"and sign their Release files, as well as providing a secure way to "
"distribute their public keys."
msgstr "在默认的设置上，当软件包是下载自无法认证的来源时，<prgn>apt-secure</prgn> 会发出警告。"
"未来的版本将可能会在下载软件包前就先强制进行检验。"
"非官方的 apt 来源的管理者欢迎您建立您的密钥并在 Release 档上签名，并能寻求安全的方式来发布他们的公钥。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:220
msgid ""
"For more information please read <prgn>apt-secure</prgn>'s manual page, the "
"<url id=\"http://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/securing-debian-howto/ch7#s-deb-"
"pack-sign\" name=\"Package signing in Debian\"> chapter of the <em>Securing "
"Debian Manual</em> and the <url id=\"http://wiki.debian.org/SecureApt\" name="
"\"wiki documentation\">."
msgstr "请阅读 <prgn>apt-secure</prgn> 的说明手册来取得更详尽的信息："
"<em>加强 Debian 安全手册</em> 的 "
"<url id=\"http://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/securing-debian-howto/ch7#s-deb-"
"pack-sign\" name=\"Debian 的软件包签名\"> 一节，以及"
"<url id=\"http://wiki.debian.org/SecureApt\" name="
"\"Wiki 文件\">。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:220
msgid "debian-volatile now an official service"
msgstr "debian-volatile 现已是官方服务"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:220
msgid ""
"The <em>debian-volatile</em> service that was introduced as an unofficial "
"service with the release of &oldreleasename;, has now become an official "
"&debian; service."
msgstr "之前在 &oldreleasename; 里所介绍的 <em>debian-volatile</em> 非官方服务"
"现已成为官方服务。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:220
msgid ""
"This means that it no longer has a <tt>.debian.net</tt> address, but now "
"uses a <tt>.debian.org</tt> address. Please make sure to update your <file>/"
"etc/apt/sources.list</file> accordingly if you were already using this "
"service."
msgstr "这表示它已不再使用 <tt>.debian.net</tt> 网址，该网址现已改为 <tt>.debian.org</tt>。"
"若您现正使用着该服务，请确认您的 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> 是否已正确对应。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:239
msgid ""
"<em>debian-volatile</em> allows users to easily update stable packages that "
"contain information that quickly goes out of date. Examples are a virus "
"scanner's signatures list or a spam filter's pattern set. For more "
"information and a list of mirrors, please see the archive's <url id=\"&url-"
"debian-volatile\" name=\"web page\">."
msgstr "<em>debian-volatile</em> 服务可以让用户轻易得进行 stable 的软件包更"
"新，因为某些软件包，像是病毒扫瞄引擎所使用的签名列表，或是垃圾邮件过滤器所使"
"用的样本信息，往往很快得就过时了。"
"请到这个档案库的 <url id=\"&url-debian-"
"volatile\" name=\"网页\"> 来取得更多的详细信息及镜像站之列表。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:239
msgid "What's new in the installation system?"
msgstr "安装系统有何改变？"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:239
msgid ""
"There has been a lot of development on the Debian Installer since its first "
"official release with &oldreleasename; resulting in both improved hardware "
"support and some exciting new features."
msgstr "自从 Debian Installer 在 &oldreleasename; 发行了首次的官方版本后，"
"针对硬件支持及一些有趣的新功能方面又经历了大量的开发工作。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:239
msgid ""
"In these Release Notes we'll only list the major changes in the installer. "
"If you are interested in an overview of the detailed changes since "
"&oldreleasename;, please check the release announcements for the "
"&releasename; beta and RC releases available from the Debian Installer's "
"<url id=\"&url-installer-news\" name=\"news history\">."
msgstr "在本发行注记里，我们只会列出在安装程序里的一些重大改变。"
"如果您想知道在 &oldreleasename; 之后它的一些详尽的改变列表，"
"请查阅在 Debian Installer 的 <url id=\"&url-installer-news\" name=\"历史旧闻\"> 上"
"有关 &releasename; beta 及 RC 版发行公告。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:239
msgid "Major changes"
msgstr "主要更改"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid "No reboot during the installation"
msgstr "在安装过程中不需重新开机"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"The installation used to be split into two parts: setting up the base system "
"and making it bootable, followed by a reboot and after that the execution of "
"<prgn>base-config</prgn> which would take care of things like user setup, "
"setup of the package management system and installation of additional "
"packages (using tasksel)."
msgstr "之前的安装程序会分成两个步骤：设置 base system 及让它能够开机、"
"接下来是重开机然后执行 <prgn>base-config</prgn> 来进行像是用户设置、"
"设置软件包的管理系统及使用 tasksel 来安装其它额外的软件包。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"For &releasename; the second stage has been integrated into Debian Installer "
"itself. This has a number of advantages, including increased security and "
"the fact that after the reboot at the end of the installation the new system "
"should already have the correct timezone and, if you installed the Desktop "
"environment, will at once start the graphical user interface."
msgstr "但从 &releasename; 开始，第二个步骤已整合至 Debian Installer 里。"
"这么做有许多的优点，包含了像是增强了安全性、在安装完成并重新开机之后，新系统"
"的时区就是正确的、如果您安装了桌面环境，将会直接启动图形界面。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid "UTF-8 encoding default for new systems"
msgstr "新系统将默认使用 UTF-8 编码"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"The installer will set up systems to use UTF-8 encoding rather than the old "
"language-specific encodings (like ISO-8859-1, EUC-JP or KOI-8)."
msgstr "安装程序将会把系统设置为使用 UTF-8 编码，而不是使用"
"专用于各语系的旧特定编码（像是 ISO-8859-1、EUC-JP 或 KOI-8）。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid "More flexible partitioning"
msgstr "更有弹性的分区程序"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"It is now possible to set up filesystems on an LVM volume using guided "
"partitioning."
msgstr "现已可以利用分区引导程序，在文件系统上使用 LVM Volume。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"The installer is also able to set up encrypted filesystems. Using manual "
"partitioning you have the choice between <tt>dm-crypt</tt> and <tt>loop-aes</"
"tt>, using a passphrase or a random key, and you can tune various other "
"options. Using guided partitioning, the installer will create an encrypted "
"LVM partition that contains any other filesystems (except <file>/boot</"
"file>) as logical volumes."
msgstr "安装程序现也可以设置加密文件系统。若使用手动硬盘分区，您可以选择使用 <tt>dm-crypt</tt> 或是 <tt>loop-aes</"
"tt>、使用密语或随机的密钥，同时您还可以调整其它各式各样的选项。"
"使用分区引导程序，安装程序将会建立一个加密 LVM 分区，它包含了其它的文件系统（除了 <file>/boot</"
"file> 之外）的 Logical Volumes。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid "Graphical user interface"
msgstr "图形安装界面"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"If you prefer a graphical user interface, try booting the installer with "
"<tt>installgui</tt>."
msgstr "如果您比较喜欢使用图形界面，请试着以 <tt>installgui</tt> 来启动安装程序。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"The functionality of the graphical installer is almost identical to the "
"regular installer, only the presentation differs. There is one exception: "
"the graphical frontend does not support setting up encrypted partitions "
"using random keys."
msgstr "除了在外表上，图形界面的安装程序和一般安装程序的功能几乎没有任何差别。"
"但只有一个地方不同：使用图形界面的安装程序无法将加密分区设置为使用随机金钥。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"Note: the graphical user interface is not available for all architectures."
msgstr "注意：并不是所有的系统平台都有图形界面可用。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"For &arch-title; a separate installation image using a graphical user "
"interface is available on an experimental basis. It is known to work on most "
"CHRP systems that have an ATI graphics card, but has been insufficiently "
"tested on &arch-title; to include it on the normal installation CDs."
msgstr "在 &arch-title; 上，只额外提供了一个仅供测试用的图形界面安装镜像文件。"
"它已知能在大多数装有 ATI 显示卡的 CHRP 系统上正常运作，但"
"在 &arch-title; 上未经完整测试之前，尚不能将它列为一般的安装 CD 之一。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"If you'd like to try the graphical installer, look for the \"gtk-miniiso\" "
"image."
msgstr "如果您很想试用图形界面的安装程序，请替而使用 \"gtk-miniiso\" 镜像文件。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid "Rescue mode"
msgstr "救援模式"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"You can use the installer to solve problems with your system, for example "
"when it refuses to boot. The first steps will be just like a regular "
"installation, but the installer will not start the partitioner. Instead it "
"will offer you a menu of rescue options."
msgstr "您可以利用安装程序来修复您系统上一些像是无法开机的问题。"
"最先的步骤会和一般的安装步骤极为类似，"
"但安装程序不会启动硬盘分区程序，"
"取而代之的它会提供一个列有救援选项的菜单。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"Activate the rescue mode by booting the installer with <tt>rescue</tt>, or "
"by adding a boot parameter <tt>rescue/enable=true</tt>."
msgstr "请以 <tt>rescue</tt> 启动安装程序，"
"或是在开机时加上 <tt>rescue/enable=true</tt> 参数，就能启动救援模式。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid "Using sudo instead of root account"
msgstr "使用 sudo 来取代 root 帐号"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"During expert installations you can choose to not set up the root account "
"(it will be locked), but instead set up <prgn>sudo</prgn> so that the first "
"user can use that for system administration."
msgstr "在 expert 安装模式中，您可以选择不要设置 root 帐号（让它因而被锁上）。"
"取而代之的是设置<prgn>sudo</prgn>，让第一个用户可以利用它来进行系统管理。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid "Cryptographic verification of downloaded packages"
msgstr "替下载到的软件包验证其验证码"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:260
msgid ""
"Packages downloaded with the installer are now cryptographically checked "
"using <prgn>secure apt</prgn> making it more difficult to compromise a "
"system being installed over the network."
msgstr "现在，经由安装程序所下载到的软件包会再利用 <prgn>secure apt</prgn> 来验证它的验证码。"
"这么一来，若想攻击经由网络安装的系统将会更加不易。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid "SELinux"
msgstr "SELinux"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid ""
"The packages needed for SELinux support have been promoted to priority "
"\"standard\". This means that they will be installed by default if you "
"select the Standard task during installation. However, SELinux support is "
"not enabled by default. If you want to secure your system using SELinux, you "
"will need to enable it manually after the installation."
msgstr "为了支持 SELinux 所需的软件包的优先权已提升为 \"标准\"。"
"这表示，如果您在安装的过程中选择了 Standard 主题，默认就会把它们安装进来。"
"然而， SELinux 默认并不会启用。"
"如果您想利用 SELinux 来强化您的系统的安全性，您必须在安装完成后手动启用。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid "Simplified mail configuration"
msgstr "简化的邮件设置"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid ""
"The installation system setups a basic configuration for the system's mail "
"server which will only provide for local e-mail delivery, if the \"standard "
"system\" is installed. The mail server will be unavailable to other systems "
"connected to the same network. If you want to configure your system to "
"handle e-mail not local to the system (either to send e-mail or to receive "
"it) you will have to reconfigure the mail system after installation."
msgstr "如果是以标准系统来进行安装的话，安装系统会将系统的邮件服务器的设置简化为只能在本机里传递邮件。"
"即使是位于相同网络上的系统也无法访问这个邮件服务器。"
"如果您想把您的系统设置为能够处理非本机的邮件（不管是寄出或接收邮件），"
"您必须在安装完成后重新设置邮件系统。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid "New languages"
msgstr "新语系"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid ""
"Thanks to the huge efforts of translators, Debian can now be installed in 47 "
"languages using the text-based installation user interface. This is six "
"languages more than in &oldreleasename;. Languages added in this release "
"include Belarusian, Esperanto, Estonian, Kurdish, Macedonian, Tagalog, "
"Vietnamese and Wolof. Languages dropped in this relase due to lack of "
"translation updates include Persian and Welsh. <![ %g-i [ If the graphical "
"user interface is used, an additional eleven languages are supported. These "
"languages can only be selected using this installer as their character sets "
"cannot be presented in a non-graphical environment. The new languages are: "
"Bengali, Dzongkha, Gujarati, Hindi, Georgian, Khmer, Malayalam, Nepali, "
"Punjabi, Tamil and Thai. ]]> Users that do not wish to use any locale can "
"now select <em>C</em> as their preferred locale in the installer's language "
"selection. More information on language coverage is available at the <url id="
"\"&url-d-i-i18n;\" name=\"d-i languages list\">."
msgstr "感谢翻译者们的辛勤努力，若使用文字界面模式安装时，Debian 支持了 47 种语系。"
"这比之前的 &oldreleasename; 再多出 6 种语系。"
"新增的语系包括了白俄罗斯语、世界语、爱沙尼亚语、库尔德语、马其顿语、塔加拉语、越南语和窝罗夫语。"
"而因为缺乏翻译的更新而在这个发行版中被废弃的语系则包括了波斯语及威尔斯语。"
"<![ %g-i [ 如果使用的是图形界面，将会再支持额外 11 种语系。"
"只能在该安装程序中选取这些语系是因为它们的字元集无法在非图形界面上显示。"
"这些新增语系包含了：孟加拉语、宗卡语、古吉拉特语、印地语、乔治亚语、高棉语、马拉雅兰语、尼泊尔语、旁遮普语、淡米尔语及泰国语。]]>"
"如果不想使用任何区域信息的用户现在可以在安装程序的语系中选择 <em>C</em> 做为偏好的区域信息。"
"更多的语系的相关信息可以由 <url id="
"\"&url-d-i-i18n;\" name=\"d-i 语系列表\">上取得。"

# type: <tag></tag>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid "Simplified localization and timezone selection"
msgstr "区域语系及时区选择上的简化"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid ""
"Configuration of language, countries and timezones have been simplified to "
"reduce the amount of information needed from the user. The installer will "
"now guess what the system's country and timezone is based on the language "
"selected, or will provide a limited selection if it cannot. Users can still "
"introduce obscure combinations if need be."
msgstr "语系、国家和时区的设置现已经过简化以减少用户必须输入的资料次数。"
"安装程序现在会根据所选取的语系自动判断系统的国家及时区，"
"或是在无法判断时提供精简后的选择列表。"
"但用户在必要时还是可以使用模糊的组合。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid "Automated installation"
msgstr "自动安装"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:335
msgid ""
"A lot of the changes mentioned in the previous section also imply changes in "
"the support in the installer for automated installation using "
"preconfiguration files. This means that if you have existing "
"preconfiguration files that worked with the &oldreleasename; installer, you "
"cannot expect these to work with the new installer without modification."
msgstr "在之前的章节中所提到的众多改变，其中也包含了在安装程序里利用事先准备好的设置文件来进行自动安装。"
"这意味着，如果您手上有着用来和 &oldreleasename; 安装程序搭配使用的事先准备好的设置文件，"
"若未经修改将难以和新的安装程序搭配使用。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:401
msgid ""
"The good news is that the <url id=\"&url-install-manual;\" name="
"\"Installation Guide\"> now has a separate appendix with extensive "
"documentation on using preconfiguration."
msgstr "好消息是，在 <url id=\"&url-install-manual;\" name="
"\"安装指南\"> 上有独立的附录，上有如何使用事先准备好的设置文件的大量信息。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:401
msgid ""
"The &releasename; installer introduces some exciting new features that allow "
"further and easier automation of installs. It also adds support for advanced "
"partitioning using RAID, LVM and encrypted LVM. See the documentation for "
"details."
msgstr "&releasename; 版的安装程序也包含了一些允许更为多样且更容易进行自动安装的新奇功能。"
"它也新支持了一些高级的硬盘分区方式，像是使用 RAID、LVM 及加密的 LVM。请参考相关文件以取得更详尽的信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:415
msgid "New installations"
msgstr "新系统的安装"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:415
msgid ""
"The Debian Installer is the official installation system for Debian. It "
"offers a variety of installation methods. Which methods are available to "
"install your system depends on your architecture."
msgstr "Debian Installer 是 Debian 的官方安装系统。"
"它提供了多种不同的安装方式。您可以依据您硬件结构的不同而有种种不同"
"的安装方式可供选择。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:415
msgid ""
"Images of the installer for &releasename; and the Installation Guide can be "
"found on the <url id=\"&url-installer;\" name=\"Debian website\">."
msgstr "可以在 <url id=\"&url-installer;\" name=\"Debian website\"> 上取得 &releasename; 的安装镜像文件及安装指南。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:415
msgid ""
"The Installation Guide is also included on the first CD/DVD of the official "
"Debian CD/DVD sets, at:"
msgstr "安装指南也同时会包含在 Debian 官方的 CD/DVD 集里的第一张 CD/DVD 的："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:428
#, no-wrap
msgid "/doc/install/manual/<var>language</var>/index.html"
msgstr "/doc/install/manual/<var>language</var>/index.html"

# type: </example></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:432
msgid ""
"You may also want to check the "
"<url id=\"&url-installer;index#errata\" name="
"\"errata\"> for debian-installer."
msgstr "您还可以到 "
"<url id=\"&url-installer;index#errata\" "
"name=\"戡误表\"> 上查看 debian-installer 的相关信息。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:432
msgid ""
"The installer can only be used to install on alpha systems which support the "
"SRM console. Be sure to switch your system to SRM before starting the "
"installation. If your machine supports only the AlphaBIOS/ARC console, you "
"can still install &releasename; using a (minimal) &oldreleasename; "
"installation and a subsequent upgrade. For more information about the "
"different consoles please read the references on the <url id=\"http://www."
"debian.org/ports/alpha\" name=\"Debian alpha port web pages\">."
msgstr "安装程序目前只能用于安装支持 SRM 控制台的 alpha 系统。在启动安装程序"
"之前，请务必记得将您的系统切换至 SRM 模式。如果您的机器只支持 AlphaBIOS/ARC "
"控制台的话，您可以借由安装（最小的）&oldreleasename; 并随即进行升级，来达到安"
"装 &releasename; 的目的。如果您想要知道各个控制台的更多相关信息，请阅读在 "
"<url id=\"http://www.debian.org/ports/alpha\" name=\"Debian alpha 平台移植网页"
"\"> 上的参考信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:432
msgid "Issues with framebuffer on &arch-title;"
msgstr "在 &arch-title; 里的 framebuffer 相关问题"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:432
msgid ""
"Because of display problems on some systems, framebuffer support is disabled "
"by default for &arch-title; for most graphics cards. This can result in ugly "
"display on systems that do properly support the framebuffer. If you see "
"display problems in the installer, you can try booting the installer with "
"the parameter <tt>framebuffer=true</tt>. Please let us know if the "
"framebuffer is not used by default, but works for your hardware."
msgstr "由于在某些系统上会有显示上的问题，所以在 &arch-title; 里，大多的显示卡默认上是不使用 "
"framebuffer 的。这会使得一些对 framebuffer 支持良好的系统上的显示效果变差。如果您在安装程序里遇到了显示上的问题，您可以试着加"
"上 <tt>framebuffer=true</tt> 这个参数来启动安装程序。"
"如果您的硬件在默认上并不使用 framebuffer 但却能正常运作，请告知我们。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:432
msgid "System improvements"
msgstr "系统改善"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:465
msgid ""
"TODO: Document improvements which users installing etch will see but not "
"those upgrading from sarge. For more information see <url id=\"http://wiki."
"debian.org/Sarge2EtchUpgrade\" name=\"the wiki pages\">."
msgstr "待完成：记述当用户安装 etch 时将会感受到但是由 sarge 升级却无法知觉的改进。"
"请参考 <url id=\"http://wiki."
"debian.org/Sarge2EtchUpgrade\" name=\"Wiki 页面\"> 以取得更详尽信息。"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid "inetd: new default is OpenBSD's"
msgstr "inetd: 现在默认是采用 OpenBSD 的"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid "portmap bound to loopback by default"
msgstr "portmap 在默认上会使用 loopback"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid "mail server not listening to connections per default"
msgstr "邮件服务器默认上不会监听任何连线"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid ""
"development packages now priority optional, will not get installed (#301138)"
msgstr "现在定开发用软件包的优先权已改为非强制性，将不会被安装 (#301138)"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid ""
"new standard task in tasksel installs all packages of priority standard and "
"higher"
msgstr "在 tasksel 中的 Standard 主题现在将会安装所有优先权为标准或以上的软件包"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid "filesystem improvements"
msgstr "文件系统的改进"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid "packages pulled in for laptops"
msgstr "笔记本电脑会安装的软件包"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid "localization-config NOT installed by d-i, needs to be run separately"
msgstr "D-I 将不再安装 localization-config，必须得分别执行"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid "Popularity contest"
msgstr "热门软件包竞赛"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid ""
"The installation system will again offer to install the <package>popularity-"
"contest</package> package. This package was not installed by default in "
"&oldreleasename; but it was installed in older releases."
msgstr "安装系统将会再次安装  <package>popularity-"
"contest</package> 软件包。在 &oldreleasename; 里，默认上并不会安装这个软件包，"
"但会在更旧的系统上被安装。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid ""
"<package>popularity-contest</package> provides the Debian project with "
"valuable information on which packages in the distribution are actually "
"used. This information is used mainly to decide the order in which packages "
"are included on installation CD-ROMs, but is also often consulted by Debian "
"developers in deciding whether or not to adopt a package that no longer has "
"a maintainer."
msgstr "<package>popularity-contest</package> 能够向 Debian 专案提供在发行版中哪些软件包正在被使用着的这个极有价"
"值信息。这个信息主要是用来决定该将哪些软件包放入安装光盘的优先顺序。而且 "
"Debian 的开发者也常常根据它的报告来决定是否该放弃某个已经没有维护者的软件包。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:468
msgid ""
"Information from <package>popularity-contest</package> is processed "
"anonymously. We would appreciate it if you would participate in this "
"official survey; you will thereby help improve Debian."
msgstr "由 <package>popularity-contest</package> 所提交的报告是匿名进行的。如果您能参与这个"
"官方的调查工作，对我们将是极大的帮助；而您也能够藉此来促使 Debian 的进步。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:510
msgid "Upgrades from previous releases"
msgstr "从先前的发行版进行升级"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid "Preparing for the upgrade"
msgstr "系统升级的准备事项"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"We suggest that before upgrading you also read the information in <ref id="
"\"information\">. That chapter covers potential issues not directly related "
"to the upgrade process but which could still be relevant."
msgstr "在进行升级之前，我们建议您能同时参阅 <ref id="
"\"information\"> 所提供的信息。在那个章节里包含了一些和升级程序无直接相关的可能潜在的相关问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"Before upgrading your system, it is strongly recommended that you make a "
"full backup, or at least backup any data or configuration information you "
"can't afford to lose. The upgrade tools and process are quite reliable, but "
"a hardware failure in the middle of an upgrade could result in a severely "
"damaged system."
msgstr "在升级您的系统之前，我们强烈建议您能进行一次完整的备份，或至少您也应该"
"把那些绝对不能出任何差错的资料和设置信息给备份起来。升级时所使用的工具和升级"
"过程应该不会出什么差错，但在升级过程中若发生了什么硬件错误可能会导致系统严重"
"受损。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"The main things you'll want to back up are the contents of <file>/etc</"
"file>, <file>/var/lib/dpkg</file> and the output of <tt>dpkg --get-"
"selections \"*\"</tt> (the quotes are important)."
msgstr "您可能会想进行备份的内容主要包括了 <file>/etc</file> 目录和 <file>/var/lib/"
"dpkg</file> 目录中的内容，以及 <tt>dpkg --get-selections \"*\"</tt>（请别忘"
"了双引号）所输出的信息。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"The upgrade process in itself does not modify anything in the <file>/home</"
"file> directory. However, some applications (e.g. parts of the Mozilla "
"suite, and the GNOME and KDE desktop environments) are known to overwrite "
"existing user settings with new defaults when a new version of the "
"application is first started by a user. As a precaution, you may want to "
"make a backup of the hidden files and directories (\"dotfiles\") in users' "
"home directories. This backup may help to restore or recreate the old "
"settings. You may also want to inform users about this."
msgstr "这个升级的程序它本身并不会修改在 <file>/home</file> 目录里的任何资料，但是已"
"知有某些应用程序（例如：部份的 Mozilla 家族程序及 GNOME、KDE 桌面环境）在用户第一次以新的"
"版本启动时，会以新的默认值覆盖用户原有的设置。为了以防万一，您也许想要针对"
"在用户的主目录里的隐藏文件及目录（\"dotfiles\"，以 . 开头的档案或目录）"
"进行备份。这个备份可以用来回复或重新建立旧有的设置。您也许有必要让用户知道"
"有这个问题存在。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"It's wise to inform all users in advance of any upgrades you're planning, "
"although users accessing your system via an <prgn>ssh</prgn> connection "
"should notice little during the upgrade, and should be able to continue "
"working. If you wish to take extra precautions, back up or unmount users' "
"partitions (<file>/home</file>) before upgrading. A reboot will not normally "
"be necessary, unless you also plan to upgrade your kernel."
msgstr "您应该在进行任何升级之前先把您的计划告知所有用户，虽然一些像是利用 <prgn>ssh</prgn> 连线来从远"
"程访问系统的用户在升级过程中可能不会发现什么异状，且他们的"
"工作也应该不会因而中断。如果您希望能采取额外的预防措施的话，请在升级前备份或卸"
"载用户的分区 (<file>/home</file>)。除非您计划同时进行内核的升级，否"
"则您在升级前后通常并不需要重新开机。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"Distribution upgrade should be done either locally from a textmode virtual "
"console (or a directly connected serial terminal), or remotely via an "
"<prgn>ssh</prgn> link."
msgstr "您应该在本机透过文字模式的虚拟控制台（或直接连线的序列终端机）、或由远程透过 "
"<prgn>ssh</prgn> 连线来进行升级至发行版的动作。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"<strong>Important!</strong> You should <em>not</em> upgrade using "
"<prgn>telnet</prgn>, <prgn>rlogin</prgn>, <prgn>rsh</prgn>, or from an X "
"session managed by <prgn>xdm</prgn>, <prgn>gdm</prgn> or <prgn>kdm</prgn> "
"etc on the machine you are upgrading. That is because each of those services "
"may well be terminated during the upgrade, which can result in an "
"<em>inaccessible</em> system that is only half-upgraded."
msgstr "<strong>极重要！</strong>您<em>不应该</em>透过 <prgn>telnet</prgn>、<prgn>rlogin</prgn>、<prgn>rsh</prgn>，"
"或是由您要进行升级的机器上的 <prgn>xdm</prgn>、<prgn>gdm</prgn> 或 <prgn>kdm</prgn> 等等所管理"
"的 X 行程来进行升级。这是因为这些服务在升级的过程中都可能会被中断，因而将会留"
"下了一个只完成部分升级而<em>无法访问</em>的系统。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"Any package installation operation must be run with superuser privileges, so "
"either login as root or use <prgn>su</prgn> or <prgn>sudo</prgn> to gain the "
"necessary access rights."
msgstr "任何软件包安装的动作都需要有系统管理者的权限才能进行，所以您必须以 root 登入，"
"或使用 <prgn>su</prgn> 或 <prgn>sudo</prgn> 来取得所需的权限。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"The upgrade has a few preconditions; you should check them before actually "
"executing the upgrade."
msgstr "升级有其必要条件，您应该在实地进行升级之前先行确认一次。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid "Make sure you have sufficient space for the upgrade"
msgstr "确认您有足够的空间可以用来进行升级"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:529
msgid ""
"You have to make sure before upgrading your system that you have sufficient "
"hard disk space when you start the full system upgrade described in <ref id="
"\"upgrading_other\">. You will first need enough hard disk on the filesystem "
"partition that holds <file>/var/</file> to temporarily download the packages "
"that will be installed in your system. After the download, you will probably "
"need more space in other filesystem partitions in order to both install "
"upgraded packages (which might contain bigger binaries or more data) and new "
"packages that will be pulled in for the upgrade. If your system does not "
"have sufficient space you might end up with an incomplete upgrade that might "
"be difficult to recover from."
msgstr "在进行系统升级之前，您必须确认在您开始进行 <ref id="
"\"upgrading_other\"> 上写的全系统升级之时，您的系统有着足够的硬盘空间。"
"首先，在包含了 <file>/var/</file> 的文件系统分区里必须拥有足够的硬盘空间"
"以容纳那些将会安装到您的系统上而暂时下载的软件包。"
"在下载完成之后，在其它的文件系统分区里您应该会需要更多的空间以用来安装升级软件包"
"（它们很可能会包含需要更大空间的档案及资料）以及在升级过程中会一并安装的新软件包。"
"如果您的系统并没有足够的空间，您可能在最后得到的是一个未完全升级却又难以还原的系统。"


# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:604
msgid ""
"Both <prgn>aptitude</prgn> and <prgn>apt</prgn> will show you detailed "
"information of the disk space needed for the installation. Before executing "
"the upgrade, you can see this estimate by running:"
msgstr "<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 及 <prgn>apt</prgn> 都会替您显示在安装时所需的硬盘空间之详尽信息。"
"在进行升级之前，您可以得到这些估算值。请执行："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:616
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# aptitude -y -s -f --with-recommends dist-upgrade\n"
"[ ... ]\n"
"XXX upgraded, XXX newly installed, XXX to remove and XXX not upgraded.\n"
"Need to get xx.xMB/yyyMB of archives. After unpacking AAAMB will be used.\n"
"Would download/install/remove packages."
msgstr "# aptitude -y -s -f --with-recommends dist-upgrade\n"
"[ ... ]\n"
"更新了 XXX、新安装了 XXX、要移除 XXX 而 XXX 将不会被升级。\n"
"必须下载 xx.xMB/yyyMB 的档案。在解压缩之后将会用掉 AAAMB。\n"
"将会进行 下载/安装/移除 软件包。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:616
msgid ""
"If you do not have enough space for the upgrade, make sure you free up space "
"beforehand. You can:"
msgstr "如果您没有足够的空间可供升级，请在事先就清出硬盘空间。您可以："

# type: <item><item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:638
msgid ""
"Remove packages that have been previously downloaded for installation (at "
"<file>/var/cache/apt/archive</file>), cleaning up the package cache by "
"running <prgn>apt-get clean</prgn>."
msgstr "移除那些之前为了用来安装而下载至 <file>/var/cache/apt/archive</file> 的软件包。"
"执行 <prgn>apt-get clean</prgn> 来清除软件包的缓存。"

# type: <item><item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:638
msgid ""
"Remove old packages you no longer use. If you have <prgn>popularity-contest</"
"prgn> installed, you can use <prgn>popcon-largest-unused</prgn> to list the "
"packages you do not use in the system that occupy the most space. You can "
"also use <prgn>deborphan</prgn> or <prgn>debfoster</prgn> to find obsolete "
"packages (see <ref id=\"obsolete\">)."
msgstr "移除那些您再也用不着的软件包。如果您安装了 <prgn>popularity-contest</"
"prgn>，您可以使用 <prgn>popcon-largest-unused</prgn> 来列出那些在系统里占有空间但您并用不着的软件包。"
"您也可以利用 <prgn>deborphan</prgn> 或 <prgn>debfoster</prgn> 来找出孤儿软件包。（请参阅："
"<ref id=\"obsolete\">）。"

# type: <item><item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:638
msgid ""
"Remove packages taking up too much space, which are not currently needed "
"(you can always reinstall them after the upgrade). You can list the packages "
"that take up most of the disk space with <prgn>dpigs</prgn> (available in "
"the <package>debian-goodies</package> package) or with <prgn>wajig</prgn> "
"(running <tt>wajig size</tt>)."
msgstr "移除占用了太多空间但目前尚用不着的软件包。"
"（您可以在升级后再把它们重新安装回来）。"
"您可以利用 <prgn>dpigs</prgn>（包含于 <package>debian-goodies</package> 之中）或 <prgn>wajig</prgn>（执行 <tt>wajig size</tt>）"
"来列出占用最多硬盘空间的软件包。"

# type: <item></item>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:638
msgid ""
"Temporarily move to another system, or permanently remove, system logs "
"residing under <file>/var/log/</file>."
msgstr "把存放在 <file>/var/log/</file> 里的系统记录文件暂时移至其它的系统，或是干脆删除它们。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:638
msgid "Support for 2.2-kernels has been dropped"
msgstr "已不再支持 2.2 系列的内核"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:638
msgid ""
"In case you run a kernel prior to 2.4.1, you need to upgrade to (at least) "
"the 2.4-series before upgrading <package>glibc</package>. This should "
"preferable be done before starting the upgrade. It is recommended you "
"directly upgrade to the 2.6-kernel (available in &oldreleasename;, instead "
"of upgrading to a 2.4-kernel series."
msgstr "如果您所运行的内核版本比 2.4.1 还旧，在升级 <package>glibc</package> 之前，您必须至少升级至 2.4 系列的内核。"
"这个动作必须在开始进行升级之前完成。"
"在此建议您能直接升级至 2.6 版的内核在 &oldreleasename; 里已有提供）而不是升级至 2.4 版的内核。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:671
msgid "Checking system status"
msgstr "检查系统的状态"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:671
msgid ""
"The upgrade process described in this chapter has been designed for upgrades "
"from \"pure\" &oldreleasename; systems without 3rd party packages. It may be "
"wise to remove these packages first."
msgstr "在这个章节中所说明的升级过程是专门为‘纯粹’的 &oldreleasename; 所写的，也就是在系统中没有安装任何其它第三方软件包。"
"先将那些软件包移除掉或许是明智的做法。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:671
msgid ""
"This procedure also assumes your system has been updated to the latest point "
"release of &oldreleasename;. If you have not done this or are unsure, follow "
"the instructions in <ref id=\"old-upgrade\">."
msgstr "而在这个过程中也假设您的系统已更新至 &oldreleasename; 的最新释出版本。"
"如果您尚未完成或是您根本无从确定，请遵循在 <ref id=\"old-upgrade\"> 里的相关说明。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:671
msgid "Disabling APT pinning"
msgstr "关闭 APT 的钉锁 (Pinning) 功能"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:671
msgid ""
"If you have configured APT to install certain packages from a distribution "
"other than stable (e.g. from testing), you may have to change your APT "
"pinning configuration (stored in <file>/etc/apt/preferences</file>) to allow "
"the upgrade of packages to the versions in the new stable release. Further "
"information on APT pinning can be found in <manref section=\"5\" name="
"\"apt_preferences\">."
msgstr "如果您将 APT 设置为可以安装除了 stable 发行版之外的软件包，（像是："
"testing），您可能必须修改您的 APT 的钉锁 (Pinning) 设置（储存于 <file>/etc/"
"apt/preferences</file> 中）来让将要进行升级的软件包能够升级至新的 stable 发行"
"版。您可以在 <manref name=\"apt_preferences\" section=\"5\"> 取得 APT 的钉锁"
"功能的更多详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:671
msgid "Checking packages status"
msgstr "检查软件包的状态"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:671
msgid ""
"Regardless of the method used for upgrading, it is recommended that you "
"check the status of all packages first, and verify that all packages are in "
"an upgradable state. The following command will show any packages which have "
"a status of Half-Installed or Failed-Config, and those with any error status."
msgstr "不论您是用什么方式进行系统的更新，我们都建议您先检查所有软件包的状态，并确认所"
"有的软件包都能够顺利升级。以下的指令会显示所有状态为半安装 (Half-Installed) "
"或设置失败 (Failed-Config) 或有其他任何错误的软件包。"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:701
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg --audit"
msgstr "# dpkg --audit"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:701
msgid ""
"You could also inspect the state of all packages on your system using "
"<prgn>dselect</prgn>, <prgn>aptitude</prgn>, or with commands such as"
msgstr "除此之外，检查系统中所有软件包状态的方法还包括使用使用 <prgn>dselect</prgn>、<prgn>aptitude</prgn>"
"、或是利用以下的指令："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:708
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg -l | pager"
msgstr "# dpkg -l | pager"

# type: </example><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:708
msgid "or"
msgstr "或是"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:714
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg --get-selections &gt; ~/curr-pkgs.txt"
msgstr "# dpkg --get-selections &gt; ~/curr-pkgs.txt"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:714
msgid ""
"It is desirable to remove any holds before upgrading. If any package that is "
"essential for the upgrade is on hold, the upgrade will fail."
msgstr "最佳的做法是在进行系统升级前将所有的软件包解除保留 (hold) 状态。如果在升级过程中有任"
"何的关键软件包的状态被设置为保留，那么升级的作业就会失败。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:714
msgid ""
"Note that <prgn>aptitude</prgn> uses a different method for registering "
"packages that are on hold than <prgn>apt-get</prgn> and <prgn>dselect</"
"prgn>. You can identify packages on hold for <prgn>aptitude</prgn> with"
msgstr "请注意到，<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 使用了和 <prgn>apt-get</prgn> 及 <prgn>dselect</"
"prgn> 迥然不同的方式来登录哪些是保留软件包。"
"您可以使用以下方式来确认哪些软件包是被保留住的："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:726
#, no-wrap
msgid "# aptitude search \"~ahold\" | grep \"^.h\""
msgstr "# aptitude search \"~ahold\" | grep \"^.h\""

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:726
msgid ""
"If you want to check which packages you had on hold for <prgn>apt-get</"
"prgn>, you should use"
msgstr "如果您想要检查那些软件包是被 <prgn>apt-get</"
"prgn> 所保留住的，请使用："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:732
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg --get-selections | grep hold"
msgstr "# dpkg --get-selections | grep hold"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:732
msgid ""
"If you changed and recompiled a package locally, and didn't rename it or put "
"an epoch in the version, you must put it on hold to prevent it from being "
"upgraded."
msgstr "如果您自行在系统中变更并重新编译了某个软件包，但却没有将其更名或在版本号码中使"
"用 epoch（自行定义版本号码），那您就必须把它设置为保留状态，以防止它被升级到"
"新的版本。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:732
msgid ""
"The \"hold\" package state for <prgn>aptitude</prgn> can be changed using "
"(replace <tt>hold</tt> with <tt>unhold</tt> to unset the \"hold\" state):"
msgstr "若想更改那些在 <prgn>aptitude</prgn> 里被保留住的软件包的状态"
"（将 <tt>hold</tt> 以 <tt>unhold</tt> 取代来消除保留状态），请使用："


# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:742
#, no-wrap
msgid "# aptitude hold <var>package_name</var>"
msgstr "# aptitude hold <var>package_name</var>"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:742
msgid ""
"If there is anything you need to fix, it is best to make sure your "
"<file>sources.list</file> still refers to &oldreleasename; as explained in "
"<ref id=\"old-sources\">."
msgstr "如果还有什么地方尚待修正，最好再次确认您的 <file>sources.list</file> 仍然是指"
"向 &oldreleasename;。请参考 <ref id=\"old-sources\"> 里的说明。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:742
msgid "Unofficial sources and backports"
msgstr "非官方的源及 backports"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:742
msgid ""
"If you have any non-Debian packages on your system, you should be aware that "
"these may be removed during the upgrade because of conflicting dependencies. "
"If these packages were installed by adding an extra package archive in your "
"<file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file>, you should check if that archive also "
"offers packages compiled for &releasename; and change the source line "
"accordingly at the same time as your source lines for Debian packages."
msgstr "如果在您的系统里安装了不是由 Debian 所提供的软件包，您必须要知道，在升级的"
"过程中它们可能会因为依赖性的关系而被移除掉。如果这些软件包是先在 <file>/etc/"
"apt/sources.list</file> 新增了额外的软件包档案库然后再加以安装的，您应该检查一"
"下那个档案库是否也提供了特别为 &releasename; 而编译的软件包，在替 Debian 变"
"更软件包来源时也同时适当得修改这些软件包的来源项目。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:768
msgid ""
"Some users may have unofficial backported \"newer\" versions of packages "
"that <em>are</em> in Debian installed on their &oldreleasename; system. Such "
"packages are most likely to cause problems during an upgrade as they may "
"result in file conflicts<footnote>Debian's package management system "
"normally does not allow a package to remove or replace a file owned by "
"another package; not unless it has been defined to replace that package.</"
"footnote>. Section <ref id=\"trouble\"> has some information on how to deal "
"with file conflicts if they should occur."
msgstr "也许有些用户会在他们的 &oldreleasename; 上安装了在 Debian <em>已</em>有软件包的非"
"官方但\"较新\" 的 backported 版本。这些软件包很可能在升级的时候产生文件冲突的问题，"
"<footnote>因为 Debian 的软件包管理程序不允许某一个软件包移除或取代了属于另一个软件"
"包的档案，除非那一个软件包本来就是用来取代这个软件包的。</footnote>。在 <ref id="
"\"trouble\"> 那一节有一些当发生了文件冲突时该如何解决的信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:768
msgid "Preparing sources for APT"
msgstr "APT 来源的准备工作"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:768
msgid ""
"Before starting the upgrade you must set up <package>apt</package>'s "
"configuration file for package lists, <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file>."
msgstr "在开始进行升级之前，您必须先在 <package>apt</package> 的设置 <file>/etc/apt/sources."
"list</file> 中设置软件包列表。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:768
msgid ""
"<package>apt</package> will consider all packages that can be found via any "
"\"<tt>deb</tt>\" line, and install the package with the highest version "
"number, giving priority to the first mentioned lines (that way, in case of "
"multiple mirror locations, you'd typically first name a local harddisk, then "
"CD-ROMs, and then HTTP/FTP mirrors)."
msgstr "<package>apt</package> 会把所有可以在 \"<tt>deb</tt>\" 行中找到的软件包全数列入考虑，并"
"安装其中版本号码最高的软件包，且会依序由列出的来源中取得软件包。（也因此，当您是由"
"许多不同位置来取得软件包时，您可以让系统依先由本机硬盘，接下来是由光盘片，然后"
"是远程 HTTP/FTP 的顺序来取得软件包）"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:768
msgid ""
"A release can often be referred to by both its codename (e.g. "
"&oldreleasename;, &releasename;) and by its status name (i.e. oldstable, "
"stable, testing, unstable). Referring to a release by its codename has the "
"advantage that you will never be surprised by a new release and for this "
"reason is the approach taken here. It does of course mean that you will have "
"to watch out for release announcements yourself. If you use the status name "
"instead, you will just see loads of updates for packages available as soon "
"as a release has happened."
msgstr "发行版通常可以使用它的开发代码名（如，&oldreleasename;、&releasename;）或是它的状态"
"名称（如，oldstable、stable、testing、unstable）来表示。使用发行版的代码有个"
"好处是您将不用为了新的发行版的到来而感到不安，这也是为什么会在此提出这个技巧"
"的原因。理所当然的，这也表示了您必须自行去注意发行版是何时发布的。如果您是替"
"而使用状态名称的，在新的发行版发布的同时，您将会立即发觉大量软件包已有新的版本"
"可供更新。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:768
msgid "Adding APT Internet sources"
msgstr "加入互联网上的 APT 软件包来源"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:768
msgid ""
"The default configuration is set up for installation from main Debian "
"Internet servers, but you may wish to modify <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</"
"file> to use other mirrors, preferably a mirror that is network-wise closest "
"to you."
msgstr "虽然系统的默认设置是使用 Debian 在互联网上的主要服务器来进行安装，但您还是"
"可能会希望修改 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> 来改为使用在网络上离您最近"
"的其它镜像站。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:809
msgid ""
"Debian HTTP or FTP mirror addresses can be found at <url id=\"&url-debian-"
"mirrors;\"> (look at the \"Full list of mirrors\" section). HTTP mirrors are "
"generally speedier than FTP mirrors."
msgstr "您也可以在 <url id=\"&url-debian-mirrors;\"> 取得 Debian 的 HTTP 或 FTP 镜像"
"站的网址（请参考【Full list of mirrors】小节）。HTTP 镜像站的传输速度通常会"
"比 FTP 镜像站来得快。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:809
msgid ""
"For example, suppose your closest Debian mirror is <tt>&url-debian-mirror-"
"eg;/</tt>. When inspecting that mirror with a web browser or FTP program, "
"you will notice that the main directories are organized like this:"
msgstr "举例来说，假设离您最近的 Debian 镜像站是 <tt>&url-debian-mirror-eg;/</tt>。当"
"您透过网页浏览器或 FTP 程序来检视这个网站时，您会发现其中的主要目录架构会像是"
"这个样子："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:821
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&url-debian-mirror-eg;/dists/&releasename;/main/binary-&architecture;/...\n"
"&url-debian-mirror-eg;/dists/&releasename;/contrib/binary-&architecture;/..."
msgstr "&url-debian-mirror-eg;/dists/&releasename;/main/binary-&architecture;/...\n"
"&url-debian-mirror-eg;/dists/&releasename;/contrib/binary-&architecture;/..."

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:821
msgid ""
"To use this mirror with <prgn>apt</prgn>, you add this line to your "
"<file>sources.list</file> file:"
msgstr "为了要让 <prgn>apt</prgn> 能够使用这个镜像站，请把以下的这一行加入您的 <file>sources.list</file> 档案之中："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:829
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb &url-debian-mirror-eg; &releasename; main contrib"
msgstr "deb &url-debian-mirror-eg; &releasename; main contrib"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:829 ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:869
msgid ""
"Note that the `<tt>dists</tt>' is added implicitly, and the arguments after "
"the release name are used to expand the path into multiple directories."
msgstr "请注意，`<tt>dists</tt>' 将会被自动加到路径中，而在发布代号之后的参数则会被用"
"来展开成多个不同目录的路径。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:829 ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:869
msgid ""
"After adding your new sources, disable the previously existing \"<tt>deb</tt>"
"\" lines in <file>sources.list</file>, by placing a hash sign (<tt>#</tt>) "
"in front of them."
msgstr "在加入了新的 APT 来源之后，请在 <file>sources.list</file> 中原有的 \"<tt>deb</tt>"
"\" 设置行前加入井字符号 (<tt>#</tt>) 以关闭这些软件包的源。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:829
msgid ""
"Any package needed for installation that is fetched from the network is "
"stored in <file>/var/cache/apt/archives</file> (and the <file>partial/</"
"file> subdirectory, during download), so you must make sure you have enough "
"space before attempting to start the installation. With a reasonably "
"extended Debian installation, you can expect at least 300 MB of downloaded "
"data."
msgstr "所有由网络上下载来的安装所需软件包都会被存放在 <file>/var/cache/apt/archives</"
"file> 目录中（而下载中的档案则会被存在 <file>partial/</file> 子目录中），所以"
"在尝试开始安装前请确认您是否有足够的硬盘空间。对一个装有大量软件包的 Debian 系"
"统来说，下载的资料量应该会超过 300 MB。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:829
msgid "Adding APT sources for a local mirror"
msgstr "增加 APT 的本机镜像软件包来源"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:829
msgid ""
"Instead of using HTTP or FTP packages mirrors, you may wish to modify <file>/"
"etc/apt/sources.list</file> to use a mirror on a local disk (possibly "
"mounted over NFS)."
msgstr "您可能也会想修改 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> 中的设置，以使用本机（像"
"是透过 NFS 挂载的）硬盘上的镜像资料来取代透过 HTTP 或 FTP 访问远程的软件包镜像"
"站。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:829
msgid ""
"For example, your packages mirror may be under <file>/var/ftp/debian/</"
"file>, and have main directories like this:"
msgstr "举例来说，如果您的软件包镜像是放在 <file>/var/ftp/debian/</file> 之下，而主要的"
"目录看起来是像这样的话："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:861
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"/var/ftp/debian/dists/&releasename;/main/binary-&architecture;/...\n"
"/var/ftp/debian/dists/&releasename;/contrib/binary-&architecture;/..."
msgstr "/var/ftp/debian/dists/&releasename;/main/binary-&architecture;/...\n"
"/var/ftp/debian/dists/&releasename;/contrib/binary-&architecture;/..."

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:861
msgid ""
"To use this with <prgn>apt</prgn>, add this line to your <file>sources.list</"
"file> file:"
msgstr "如果要和 <prgn>apt</prgn> 搭配使用，请把下行加入 <file>sources.list</"
"file> 文件之中："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:869
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb file:/var/ftp/debian &releasename; main contrib"
msgstr "deb file:/var/ftp/debian &releasename; main contrib"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:869
msgid "Adding APT source from CD-ROM or DVD"
msgstr "增加 APT 的 CD-ROM 或 DVD 的软件包来源"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:869
msgid ""
"If you want to use CDs <em>only</em>, comment out the existing \"<tt>deb</tt>"
"\" lines in <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> by placing a hash sign "
"(<tt>#</tt>) in front of them."
msgstr "如果光盘是<em>唯一</em>您想使用的源，请在 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> 中"
"原有的 \"<tt>deb</tt>\" 设置行前加入井字符号 (<tt>#</tt>) 以关闭这些软件包来源。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:888
msgid ""
"Make sure there is a line in <file>/etc/fstab</file> that enables mounting "
"your CD-ROM drive at the <file>/cdrom</file> mount point (the exact <file>/"
"cdrom</file> mount point is required for <prgn>apt-cdrom</prgn>). For "
"example, if <file>/dev/hdc</file> is your CD-ROM drive, <file>/etc/fstab</"
"file> should contain a line like:"
msgstr "请确定在 <file>/etc/fstab</file> 中有着能让您的光盘机挂载在 <file>/cdrom</"
"file> 这个挂载点下的项目（<prgn>apt-cdrom</prgn> 限定挂载点必须是 <file>/cdrom</"
"file>）。举例来说，如果您的光盘机的设备是 <file>/dev/hdc</file>，那么 <file>/"
"etc/fstab</file> 中就应该要有像这样的一行："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:896
#, no-wrap
msgid "/dev/hdc /cdrom auto defaults,noauto,ro 0 0"
msgstr "/dev/hdc /cdrom auto defaults,noauto,ro 0 0"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:896
msgid ""
"Note that there must be <em>no spaces</em> between the words <tt>defaults,"
"noauto,ro</tt> in the fourth field."
msgstr "请注意在第四栏的 <tt>defaults,noauto,ro</tt> 的字中间一定<em>不能参杂空白字"
"符</em>。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:896
msgid "To verify it works, insert a CD and try running"
msgstr "要确认您的设置是否正确，请放入一张光盘，并试着执行"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:905
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# mount /cdrom    # this will mount the CD to the mount point\n"
"# ls -alF /cdrom  # this should show the CD's root directory\n"
"# umount /cdrom   # this will unmount the CD"
msgstr "# mount /cdrom    # 这样将会将这张 CD 挂载在该挂载点上\n"
"# ls -alF /cdrom  # 这样将会列出 CD 的根目录\n"
"# umount /cdrom   # 这样将会卸载这张 CD"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:905
msgid "Next, run:"
msgstr "接下来对每一张 Debian 的程序光盘执行"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:913
#, no-wrap
msgid "# apt-cdrom add"
msgstr "# apt-cdrom add"

# type: </example></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:913
msgid ""
"for each Debian Binary CD-ROM you have, to add the data about each CD to "
"APT's database."
msgstr "来把每一张光盘的资料加到 APT 的数据库中。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:913
msgid "Upgrading packages"
msgstr "进行软件包的升级"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:913
msgid ""
"The recommended way to upgrade from previous &debian; releases is to use the "
"package management tool <prgn>aptitude</prgn>. This program makes safer "
"decisions about package installations than running <prgn>apt-get</prgn> "
"directly."
msgstr "若要从旧有的 &debian; 发行软件包进行升级时，建议的方法是使用软件包管理工具 "
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn>。这个程序在软件包安装上会比起直接执行 <prgn>apt-get</"
"prgn> 来得安全。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:913
msgid ""
"Don't forget to mount all needed partitions (notably the root and <file>/"
"usr</file> partitions) read-write, with a command like:"
msgstr "不要忘了用类似以下的口令把所有会用到的分区（特别是 <file>/usr</file> 和 "
"root 分区）重新以可读写的模式挂载："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:933
#, no-wrap
msgid "# mount -o remount,rw /<var>mountpoint</var>"
msgstr "# mount -o remount,rw /<var>mountpoint</var>"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:933
msgid ""
"Next you should double check that the APT source entries (in <file>/etc/apt/"
"sources.list</file>) refer either to \"<tt>&releasename;</tt>\" or to "
"\"<tt>stable</tt>\". Note: source lines for a CD-ROM will often refer to "
"\"<tt>unstable</tt>\"; although this may be confusing, you should <em>not</"
"em> change it."
msgstr "接下来，您必须再次确认在 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> 中的 APT 来源项目"
"是指向 \"<tt>&releasename;</tt>\" 或是 <tt>'stable'</tt>。请注意，CD-ROM 的来源项"
"目通常会指向 \"<tt>unstable</tt>\"，虽然您可能会觉得这有点奇怪，但您<em>不</em>应该"
"去加以更动。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:933
msgid ""
"It is strongly recommended that you use the <prgn>/usr/bin/script</prgn> "
"program to record a transcript of the upgrade session. Then if a problem "
"occurs, you will have a log of what happened, and if needed, can provide "
"exact information in a bug report. To start the recording, type:"
msgstr "我们强烈建议您使用 <prgn>/usr/bin/script</prgn> 这个程序来记录升级的完整过"
"程。因为一旦发生了任何问题，您手上就会有发生了什么问题的确实记录，而在必要之"
"时，在错误报告中也能据此提供确实的信息。若要开始进行记录，请使用"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:949
#, no-wrap
msgid "# script -t -a ~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.typescript 2>~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.timing"
msgstr "# script -t -a ~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.typescript 2>~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.timing"

# type: </example></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:949
msgid ""
"or similar. Do not put the typescript file in a temporary directory such as "
"<file>/tmp</file> or <file>/var/tmp</file> (files in those directories may "
"be deleted during the upgrade or during any restart)."
msgstr "或类似的指令。请不要把记录文件放在像是 <file>/tmp</file> 或 <file>/var/tmp</"
"file> 之类的暂存目录下（这些目录中的文件可能会在升级的过程中或在重新开机时"
"被清除掉）。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:949
msgid ""
"The typescript will also allow you to review information that has scrolled "
"off-screen. Just switch to VT2 (using <tt>Alt-F2</tt>) and, after logging "
"in, use <tt>less -R ~root/upgrade-to-&releasename;.typescript</tt> to view "
"the file."
msgstr "而这些记录文件也可以让您重新检查那些已被卷出屏幕之外的信息。请切换至第二个虚拟终端"
"机 VT2（使用 <tt>Alt-F2</tt>），在登录之后，使用 <tt>less ~root/upgrade-to-"
"&releasename;.typescript</tt> 来浏览这个文件。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:949
msgid ""
"After you have completed the upgrade, you can stop <prgn>script</prgn> by "
"typing <tt>exit</tt> at the prompt."
msgstr "在您完成升级操作后，您可以借由在命令行上输入 <tt>exit</tt> 来关闭 <prgn>script</prgn>。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:968
msgid ""
"If you have used the <em>-t</em> switch for <prgn>script</prgn> you can use "
"the <prgn>scriptreplay</prgn> program to replay the whole session:"
msgstr "如果您在 <prgn>script</prgn> 上使用了 <em>-t</em> 参数，"
"您可以利用 <prgn>scriptreplay</prgn> 程序来重新播放整个过程："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:972
#, no-wrap
msgid "# scriptreplay ~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.timing 2>~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.typescript"
msgstr "# scriptreplay ~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.timing 2>~/upgrade-to-&releasename;.typescript"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:972
msgid "Updating the package list"
msgstr "更新软件包的列表"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:972
msgid ""
"First the list of available packages for the new release needs to be "
"fetched. This is done by executing<footnote>We use <prgn>apt-get</prgn> for "
"this because the &oldreleasename; version <prgn>aptitude</prgn> may fail "
"when new sources have been added to <file>sources.list</file>.</footnote>:"
msgstr "首先，必须从新的发行版中取得可使用软件包的列表。要达到这个目的，请执行"
"<footnote>我们在此使用 <prgn>apt-get</prgn> 是因为当新的来源被加入 <file>sources.list</file> 后，"
"&oldreleasename; 版的 <prgn>aptitude</prgn> 可能会无法正常运作。</"
"footnote>："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:985 ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2161
#, no-wrap
msgid "# apt-get update"
msgstr "# apt-get update"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:995
msgid "Upgrading aptitude"
msgstr "更新 aptitude"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:995
msgid ""
"Upgrade tests have shown that &releasename;'s version of <prgn>aptitude</"
"prgn> is better at solving the complex dependencies during an upgrade than "
"either <prgn>apt-get</prgn> or &oldreleasename;'s <prgn>aptitude</prgn>. It "
"should therefore be upgraded first using:"
msgstr "在进行升级的测试中显示，&releasename; 版的  <prgn>aptitude</"
"prgn> 在升级过程中，对于"
"处理复杂的依赖上的问题，它的表现比 <prgn>apt-get</prgn> 或 &oldreleasename; 版的 "
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 更为优异。因此，您可以先利用以下指令进行升级："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1004
#, no-wrap
msgid "# aptitude install aptitude"
msgstr "# aptitude install aptitude"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1004
msgid ""
"You will be shown a list of the changes that will be made and asked you to "
"confirm them. You should take a careful look at the proposed changes, "
"especially packages that will be removed by the upgrade, before you confirm."
msgstr "您应该会得到将会进行什么样的改变的一串联表，并询问您是否要继续进行。在您确认"
"之前，您应该仔细得查看将会进行什么样的改变，尤其要注意在升级的过程中将会被移"
"除掉的那些软件包。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1004
msgid ""
"In some cases if a large number of packages is listed for removal, you may "
"be able to reduce this list by \"pre-upgrading\" selected other packages "
"alongside <package>aptitude</package>. An example may clarify this. During "
"upgrade tests for systems having KDE installed, we have seen that this step "
"would cause removal of a large number of KDE packages and/or perl. The "
"solution proved to be to <tt>install aptitude perl</tt> instead of "
"<tt>install aptitude</tt>."
msgstr "在某些状况之下，会列出来一大串将会被移除的软件包的列表。您可以借由使用 \"预先升"
"级, pre-upgrading\" 的方式，也就是在安装 <package>aptitude</package> 的同时再多安装另"
"一个特定的软件包，来减少这些会被移除的软件包的列表。用一个范例来说明可能会比较好"
"理解。在一个安装了 KDE 的系统的升级测试中，我们会发现在这个步骤里，将会移除一"
"大堆的 KDE 软件包及/或 perl。而在此提供的解决方案就是使用 <tt>install aptitude "
"perl</tt> 来取代 <tt>install aptitude</tt> 指令。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1004
msgid "Upgrading the rest of the system"
msgstr "升级系统的其它部份"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1004
msgid ""
"You are now ready to continue with the main part of the upgrade. Execute:"
msgstr "那么，现在已经准备好可以进行升级作业的重头戏了。请执行："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1027
#, no-wrap
msgid "# aptitude -f --with-recommends dist-upgrade"
msgstr "# aptitude -f --with-recommends dist-upgrade"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1027
msgid ""
"This will perform a complete upgrade of the system, i.e. install the newest "
"available versions of all packages, and resolve all possible dependency "
"changes between packages in different releases. If necessary, it will "
"install some new packages (usually new library versions, or renamed "
"packages), and remove any conflicting obsoleted packages (such as "
"<package>console-tools-libs</package>)."
msgstr "这将会在您的系统上进行完整的更新，也就是安装所有软件包目前所提供的最新版本，并解决"
"软件包在不同发行版之间可能会有的依赖性问题。如果有必要的话，它也会安装一些新的"
"软件包（通常是新版的函数库或是被更名的软件包），并移除任何和新版软件包发生冲突的过"
"时软件包（像是 <package>console-tools-libs</package>。）"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1027
msgid ""
"When upgrading from a set of CD-ROMs, you will be asked to insert specific "
"CDs at several points during the upgrade. You might have to insert the same "
"CD multiple times; this is due to inter-related packages that have been "
"spread out over the CDs."
msgstr "如果您是从光盘组来进行升级的话，系统将会在升级进行时不时要求您放入某张特定的"
"光盘片。您可能会需要反覆放入同一张光盘数次；这是由于相关的软件包被分散在多张光"
"碟之中所造成的。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1027
msgid ""
"New versions of currently installed packages that cannot be upgraded without "
"changing the install status of another package will be left at their current "
"version (displayed as \"held back\"). This can be resolved by either using "
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn> to choose these packages for installation or by trying "
"<tt>aptitude -f install <var>package</var></tt>."
msgstr "如果升级某些已安装的软件包至新版本时会改变其他软件包的安装状态的话，这些软件包就会"
"被保留在原来的状态（并显示为 \"留置, held back\"）。可以使用 <prgn>aptitude</"
"prgn> 选择这些软件包并进行安装，或是试着键入 <tt>aptitude -f install "
"<var>package</var></tt>，就能够解决这个问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1027
msgid ""
"The <tt>--fix-broken</tt> (or just <tt>-f</tt>) option causes <package>apt</"
"package> to attempt to correct a system with broken dependencies in place. "
"<package>apt</package> does not allow broken package dependencies to exist "
"on a system."
msgstr "<tt>--fix-broken</tt>（或只是 <tt>-f</tt>）选项会让 <package>apt</"
"package> 尝试适当地修正系统"
"中错误的依赖关系。<package>apt</package> 不允许系统中存在任何在依赖关系上的错误。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1027
msgid "Possible issues during upgrade"
msgstr "在升级过程中可能会发生的问题"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1027
msgid ""
"If an operation using <prgn>aptitude</prgn>, <prgn>apt-get</prgn> or "
"<prgn>dpkg</prgn> fails with the error"
msgstr "如果在使用 <prgn>aptitude</prgn>、<prgn>apt-get</prgn> 或 <prgn>dpkg</prgn> 的过程中失败了并显"
"示以下错误"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1062
#, no-wrap
msgid "E: Dynamic MMap ran out of room"
msgstr "E: Dynamic MMap ran out of room"

# type: </example><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1062
msgid ""
"the default cache space is insufficient. You can solve this by either "
"removing or commenting lines you don't need in <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</"
"file> or by increasing the cache size. The cache size can be increased by "
"setting <tt>APT::Cache-Limit</tt> in <file>/etc/apt/apt.conf</file>. The "
"following command will set it to a value that should be sufficient for the "
"upgrade:"
msgstr "那么，就表示默认的缓存空间不够了。您可以从 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</"
"file> 中将您不需要的项目加上注解或是干脆将它移去，或是增加缓存空间，来解决这"
"个问题。可以经由设置 <file>/etc/apt/apt.conf</file> 里的 <tt>APT::Cache-Limit</tt> 来增加缓存空间。假设您还没有在这个文件里替这个变数设置任何的数值，那么"
"以下的命令应该可以替升级的动作设置足够的缓存空间：<example>"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1071
#, no-wrap
msgid "# echo 'APT::Cache-Limit \"12500000\";' >> /etc/apt/apt.conf"
msgstr "# echo 'APT::Cache-Limit \"12500000\";' >> /etc/apt/apt.conf"

# type: </example></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1071
msgid "This assumes that you do not yet have this variable set in that file."
msgstr "在此则假设了您尚未在该文件中设置这个变数。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1071
msgid ""
"Sometimes it's necessary to enable APT::Force-LoopBreak option in APT to be "
"able to temporarily remove an essential package due to a Conflicts/Pre-"
"Depends loop. <prgn>aptitude</prgn> will alert you of this and abort the "
"upgrade. You can work around that by specifying <tt>-o APT::Force-"
"LoopBreak=1</tt> option on <prgn>aptitude</prgn> command line."
msgstr "有时候您会需要启用 APT::Force-LoopBreak 选项让 APT 暂时移除某个重要的软件包，以"
"解决循环的 相互冲突(Conflicts) / 相互依赖(Pre-Depends) 关系。<prgn>aptitude</prgn> "
"会对此提出警告，并终止升级的进行。您可以在 <<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 的命令行中加入 "
"<tt>-o APT::Force-LoopBreak=1</tt> 来解决这个问题。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1081
msgid ""
"It is possible that a system's dependency structure can be so corrupt as to "
"require manual intervention. Usually this means using <prgn>aptitude</prgn> "
"or"
msgstr "系统中的依赖关系也可能混乱到需要手动介入才得以解决。通常这代表您需要使用 "
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 或"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1087
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg --remove <var>package_name</var>"
msgstr "# dpkg --remove <var>package_name</var>"

# type: </example><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1087
msgid "to eliminate some of the offending packages, or"
msgstr "来清除一些会造成问题的软件包，或"

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1093
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# aptitude --fix-broken install\n"
"# dpkg --configure --pending"
msgstr "# aptitude --fix-broken install\n"
"# dpkg --configure --pending"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1093
msgid ""
"In extreme cases you might have to force re-installation with a command like"
msgstr "在极端的情况下，您可能需要利用类似以下的指令来强制进行重新安装的动作："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1101
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg --install <var>/path/to/package_name.deb</var>"
msgstr "# dpkg --install <var>/path/to/package_name.deb</var>"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1101
msgid ""
"File conflicts should not occur if you upgrade from a \"pure\" "
"&oldreleasename; system, but can occur if you have unofficial backports "
"installed. A file conflict will result in an error like:"
msgstr "如果您是由一个 \"纯粹\" 的 &oldreleasename; 进行升级的话，应该不会有文件冲突"
"的情况发生；但如果您安装了非官方的 backports 软件包时就不一定了。如果发生文件冲"
"突时，会产生类似以下的错误："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Unpacking replacement <var>&lt;package-foo&gt;</var> ...\n"
"dpkg: error processing <var>&lt;package-name-for-foo&gt;</var> (--unpack):\n"
" trying to overwrite `<var>&lt;some-file-name&gt;</var>',\n"
" which is also in package <var>&lt;package-bar&gt;</var>"
msgstr "解开并置换 <var>&lt;package-foo&gt;</var> ...\n"
"dpkg: 程序错误 <var>&lt;package-name-for-foo&gt;</var> (--unpack):\n"
" 尝试覆写 `<var>&lt;some-file-name&gt;</var>',\n"
" 而同时存在于软件包 <var>&lt;package-bar&gt;</var>"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1109
msgid ""
"You can try to solve a file conflict by forcibly removing the package "
"mentioned on the <em>last</em> line of the error message:"
msgstr "您可以强制移除出现在错误信息里最<em>后</em>一行的那个软件包，以解决文件冲突的问题："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1119
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg -r --force-depends <var>package_name</var>"
msgstr "# dpkg -r --force-depends <var>package_name</var>"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1119
msgid ""
"After fixing things up, you should be able to resume the upgrade by "
"repeating the previously described <tt>aptitude</tt> commands."
msgstr "在问题都修正了之后，您就应该可以重新输入先前所描述的 <tt>aptitude</tt> 指令并"
"继续升级的工作了。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1119
msgid ""
"During the upgrade, you will be asked questions regarding the configuration "
"or re-configuration of several packages. When you are asked if any file in "
"the <file>/etc/init.d</file> or <file>/etc/terminfo</file> directories, or "
"the <file>/etc/manpath.config</file> file should be replaced by the package "
"maintainer's version, it's usually necessary to answer `yes' to ensure "
"system consistency. You can always revert to the old versions, since they "
"will be saved with a <tt>.dpkg-old</tt> extension."
msgstr "在升级的过程中，系统可能会询问您一些问题，以便能对软件包进行设置或重新设置。当"
"您被问到是否要把在 <file>/etc/init.d</file> 或 <file>/etc/terminfo</file> 目"
"录中的文件或是 <file>/etc/manpath.config</file> 这个文件置换成软件包维护者所提"
"供的版本时，您通常必须回答 `yes' 以维护系统的一致性。您可以在稍后再复原为旧的"
"设置，因为它们都会以在档名后附加 <tt>.dpkg-old</tt> 的方式给保留下来。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1119
msgid ""
"If you're not sure what to do, write down the name of the package or file, "
"and sort things out at a later time. You can search in the typescript file "
"to review the information that was on the screen during the upgrade."
msgstr "如果您不太确定要怎么做的话，把软件包或文件的名称写下来，等稍后再慢慢将头绪理出来。您可以在记录档中搜寻，以便能重新检视在系统升级时出现在屏幕上的信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1119
msgid "Upgrading your kernel and related packages"
msgstr "替您的内核及相关软件包进行升级"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1150
msgid ""
"You should upgrade the Linux kernel separately from the rest of your "
"packages. You may wish to do so yourself, either by installing one of the "
"<package>linux-image-*</package> packages or by compiling a customized "
"kernel from sources. Please read the information in this section about "
"potential issues with kernel upgrades."
msgstr "您应该在将您的软件包升级完毕后再各别进行 Linux 内核的升级。"
"您也许会想要自行手动进行，像是安装某个 <package>linux-image-*</package> 软件包，或是从原始码中编译一个自订"
"的内核。"
"请参阅本节中有关在升级内核时所可能遇到的潜在问题以及相关信息。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1150
msgid ""
"All Linux kernel packages have been renamed from <package>kernel-*</package> "
"to <package>linux-*</package> to clean up the namespace."
msgstr "为了避免名称上的混淆，所有的 Linux 内核软件包已由 <package>kernel-*</package> 更名为 <package>linux-*</package>。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1167
msgid ""
"If you are currently using a kernel from the 2.4 series, the older stable "
"Linux kernel series, you should upgrade to a 2.6 series kernel, as 2.4 is no "
"longer supported in &releasename;. If you are currently using a kernel from "
"the 2.2 series, you must upgrade to (at least) the 2.4 series, preferably to "
"a 2.6 series kernel, prior to upgrading your packages. Some general issues "
"associated with an upgrade to 2.6 are documented in <ref id=\"upgrade-to-2.6"
"\">."
msgstr "如果您还在使用着 2.4 系列的内核，也就是旧的稳定版的 Linux内核 系列，"
"您应该升级到 2.6 系列的内核，因为 2.4 系列已不再被 &releasename; 支持了。"
"如果您还在使用着 2.2 系列的内核，在更新您的软件包之前，您（至少）应该升级到 2.4 系列的内核，"
"若能升级到 2.6 系列的内核就再好不过了。"
"一些在升级至 2.6 时所会伴随出现的常见问题已记述在 <ref id=\"upgrade-to-2.6"
"\"> 了。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1167
msgid "Upgrading from a 2.6 kernel"
msgstr "由某个 2.6 版的内核进行升级"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1180
msgid ""
"If you are currently running a 2.6 series kernel from &oldreleasename; you "
"will have to upgrade to the latest version of <package>coreutils</package> "
"before you upgrade to the 2.6 series kernel available in &releasename;. In "
"order to do this you first have to do a minimal upgrade of the system, a "
"full upgrade of the system packages (as described in <ref id="
"\"upgradingpackages\">) is not an option since the <prgn>udev</prgn> version "
"in &releasename; does not support 2.6.8 kernels, conversely the <prgn>udev</"
"prgn> version in &oldreleasename; will not work properly with the latest "
"kernels."
msgstr "如果您正在使用着由 &oldreleasename; 所提供的 2.6 系列的内核，"
"在您升级至 &releasename; 所提供的 2.6 系列的内核之前，您必须先升级到最新版本的 <package>coreutils</package>。"
"为此，您首先必须替您的系统做个小小的升级。"
"无法直接进行全系统软件包升级的原因是因为在 &releasename; 里的 <prgn>udev</prgn> 版本并不支持 2.6.8 版的内核，"
"换言之，在 &oldreleasename; 里的 <prgn>udev</"
"prgn> 版本将无法在最新的内核上正常运作。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1180
msgid ""
"<em>TODO</em>: Describe the steps for this minimal upgrade, should take care "
"of glibc, initrd-tools and udev + linux-image 2.6."
msgstr "<em>待完成</em>：说明最低升级的步骤，应对 glibc、initrd-tools 及 udev + linux-image 2.6 特别注意。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid "initrd-tools deprecated"
msgstr "initrd-tools 已被废弃"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid ""
"<package>initrd-tools</package> is no longer supported and has been "
"superseded by <package>initramfs-tools</package> and <package>yaird</"
"package>. Upgrading to an &releasename; kernel will cause <package>initramfs-"
"tools</package> to be installed by default. <![ %defaulted-2.4 [ If you are "
"upgrading from a 2.4 kernel to a 2.6 kernel for the first time, you must use "
"<package>initramfs-tools</package>. Using <package>yaird</package> will "
"cause linux-image-2.6 installations to fail if you are running a 2.2 or 2.4 "
"kernel. ]]>"
msgstr "<package>initrd-tools</package> 已不再被支持且已被 <package>initramfs-tools</package> 及 <package>yaird</"
"package> 所取代。"
"若要升级 &releasename; 版的内核 将会默认安装 <package>initramfs-"
"tools</package>。<![ %defaulted-2.4 [ 如果这是您第一次由 2.4 版升级至 2.6 版的内核，"
"您必须使用 <package>initramfs-tools</package>。如果您正在使用着 2.2 或 2.4 版的内核，使用 <package>yaird</package> 将会导致 linux-image-2.6 安装失败。]]>"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid "devfs deprecated"
msgstr "devfs 已被废弃"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid ""
"&releasename; no longer provides support for <prgn>devfs</prgn>. It is "
"recommended that users switch to <package>udev</package> for dynamic <file>/"
"dev</file> management. Debian kernels no longer include support for "
"<prgn>devfs</prgn>, so <prgn>devfs</prgn> users will need to convert their "
"systems manually before upgrading to an &releasename; kernel."
msgstr "&releasename; 已不再提供对 <prgn>devfs</prgn> 的支持。"
"在此建议用户替而使用 <package>udev</package> 来进行动态的 <file>/"
"dev</file> 管理。Debian内核 已不再提供对 <prgn>devfs</prgn> 的支持，"
"所以 <prgn>devfs</prgn> 的用户在升新至 &releasename; 的内核之前必须手动进行转换。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid ""
"If you see the string 'devfs' in <file>/proc/mounts</file>, you are most "
"likely using <prgn>devfs</prgn>. Any config files that reference "
"<prgn>devfs</prgn> style names will need to be adjusted to use <prgn>udev</"
"prgn> style names. Files that are most likely to refer to <prgn>devfs</prgn> "
"style device names are <file>/etc/fstab</file>, <file>/etc/lilo.conf</file>, "
"<file>/boot/grub/menu.lst</file>, etc."
msgstr "如果您在 <file>/proc/mounts</file> 里有看到 'devfs' 这个字符串，那么您十之八九正在使用着 <prgn>devfs</prgn>。"
"所有还在使用着 <prgn>devfs</prgn> 版的名称的设置必须要修正为指向 <prgn>udev</prgn> 版的名称。"
"一些很可能会使用着 <prgn>devfs</prgn>版的设备名称有 <file>/etc/fstab</file>、<file>/etc/lilo.conf</file>、<file>/boot/grub/menu.lst</file> 等等。 "

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid ""
"More information about potential issues is available in bug report <url id="
"\"http://bugs.debian.org/341152\" name=\"#341152\">."
msgstr "可以在错误回报 <url id="
"\"http://bugs.debian.org/341152\" name=\"#341152\"> 里取得一些可能的问题的更详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid "Standard kernels have SMP abilities"
msgstr "标准的内核将支持 SMP"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid ""
"Multiprocessor systems no longer require a *-smp flavour of the Linux "
"kernel. For &arch-title; linux-image packages without the -smp suffix "
"support both uniprocessor and multiprocessor systems."
msgstr "多处理器的系统已不再需要使用 *-smp 类别的 Linux内核 了。"
"在 &arch-title; 里，没有加上 -smp 字尾的 linux-image 软件包将会同时支持了单处理器和多处理器。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid "386 kernel flavour deprecated"
msgstr "386 类别的内核已被废弃"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid ""
"Support for the 80386 sub-archicture for &arch-title; has been dropped in "
"&releasename;. The 386 kernel flavor is no longer supported and has been "
"replaced by the new 486 flavour."
msgstr "在 &releasename;. 里，&arch-title; 对于 80386 子平台的支持已经终止。"
"386 类别的内核已被废弃且已被新的 486 类别所取代。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid "Device enumeration reordering"
msgstr "重新排序设备列表"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1195
msgid ""
"&releasename; features a more robust mechanism for hardware discovery than "
"previous releases. However, this may cause changes in the order devices are "
"discovered on your system affecting the order in which device names are "
"assigned. For example, if you have two network adapters that are associated "
"with two different drivers, the devices eth0 and eth1 refer to may be "
"swapped. Please note that the new mechanism means that if you e.g. exchange "
"ethernet adapters in a running &releasename; system, the new adapter will "
"also get a new interface name."
msgstr "比起先前的释出版本，&releasename; 在判断硬件设备方面提供了一个更为稳健的机制。"
"然而，这将可能会改变在您的系统上所找到的硬件的顺序，进而会影响到所使用的设备名称。"
"比如说，如果您有着两片使用着不同的驱动程序的网络卡，那么 eth0 和 eth1 的顺序很可能会互换。"
"请注意到，新的机制也代表了如果您像是置换了正在运作中的 &releasename; 系统上的网络卡，"
"新的网络卡将会拿到一个新的界面名称。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1267
msgid ""
"For network devices, you can avoid this reordering by using the "
"<prgn>ifrename</prgn> utility to bind physical devices to specific names at "
"boot time. See <manref section=\"8\" name=\"ifrename\"> and <manref section="
"\"5\" name=\"iftab\"> for more information. You can also avoid this by using "
"<prgn>udev</prgn> rules, more specifically, through the definitions at "
"<file>/etc/udev/rules.d/z25_persistent-net.rules</file><footnote> The rules "
"there are automatically generated to have persistent names for network "
"interfaces</footnote>. Both alternatives (<prgn>ifrename</prgn> and "
"<prgn>udev</prgn>) should not be used at the same time."
msgstr "对于网络设备而言，您可以使用 <prgn>ifrename</prgn> 工具程序在开机时替实体设备指定特定的名称来避开这个问题。"
"请参阅 <manref section=\"8\" name=\"ifrename\"> 及 <manref section="
"\"5\" name=\"iftab\"> 以取得更详尽的信息。"
"您也可以利用 <prgn>udev</prgn> 的规则；更明确得说，"
"经由 <file>/etc/udev/rules.d/z25_persistent-net.rules</file> 里的定义来避开这个问题。"
"<footnote>在此的规则是替网络界面自动产生连续的名称</footnote>。这两个方案（<prgn>ifrename</prgn> 及 <prgn>udev</prgn>）只能择一使用，无法同时采用。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid ""
"For storage devices, you can avoid this reordering by using "
"<package>initramfs-tools</package> and configuring it to load storage device "
"driver modules in the same order they are currently loaded. To do this, "
"identify the order the storage modules on your system were loaded by looking "
"at the output of <prgn>lsmod</prgn>. <prgn>lsmod</prgn> lists modules in the "
"reverse order that they were loaded in, i.e., the first module in the list "
"was the last one loaded."
msgstr "在储存设备上，您可以借由 <package>initramfs-tools</package> 并将其设置为使用和目前相同的载入顺序来载入储存设备的驱动模块以避开这个问题。"
"为此，您可以查看 <prgn>lsmod</prgn> 的输出来确认您的系统载入储存设备的驱动模块的顺序。"
"<prgn>lsmod</prgn> 会以相反的顺序列出载入的模块。也就是说，在列表中的第一个模块是最后载入的。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid ""
"However, removing and reloading modules after initial boot will affect this "
"order. Also, your kernel may have some drivers linked statically, and these "
"names will not appear in the output of <prgn>lsmod</prgn>. You may be able "
"to decipher these driver names and load order from looking at <file>/var/log/"
"kern.log</file>, or the output of <prgn>dmesg</prgn>."
msgstr "但是，在开机后移除或重新载入模块将会影响这份列表的顺序。"
"同时，您的内核也许会以静态连结至某些模块，所以这些名称将不会出现在 <prgn>lsmod</prgn> 的输出里。"
"您也可以经由查看 <file>/var/log/"
"kern.log</file> 或 <prgn>dmesg</prgn> 的输出来辨认出这些驱动的名称及载入顺序。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid ""
"Add these module names to <file>/etc/initramfs-tools/modules</file> in the "
"order they should be loaded at boot time. Some module names may have changed "
"between &oldreleasename; and &releasename;. For example, sym53c8xx_2 has "
"become sym53c8xx."
msgstr "将这些模块名称以它们在开机时应有的载入顺序新增到 <file>/etc/initramfs-tools/modules</file> 里。"
"有些模块名称在 &oldreleasename; 及 &releasename; 里是有所不同的。比如说，sym53c8xx_2 已变成了 sym53c8xx。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid ""
"You will then need to regenerate your initramfs image(s) by executing "
"<tt>update-initramfs -k all</tt>."
msgstr "然后，您将必须执行 <tt>update-initramfs -k all</tt> 来重新产生您的 initramfs 镜像。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid ""
"Once you are running an &releasename; kernel and <prgn>udev</prgn>, you may "
"reconfigure your system to access disks by an alias that is not dependent "
"upon driver load order. These aliases reside in the <file>/dev/disk/</file> "
"hierarchy."
msgstr "若您使用的是 &releasename; 版的内核 及 <prgn>udev</prgn>，"
"您也许要重新设置您的系统以便能以和驱动载入顺序无关的别名来进行访问。"
"这些别名会分门别类得放在 <file>/dev/disk/</file> 里。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid "Serial device reordering"
msgstr "重新排序串联设备"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid ""
"If you have an HP machine and you're using the MP serial console port (the "
"connector labelled \"console\" on the 3-headed cable), this kernel upgrade "
"will break your console!"
msgstr "如果您手上的是 HP 的机器且您正在使用 MP 串联控制台连接埠（在三头的连接线上，其连接器有标注‘console’者），"
"内核的升级将会中断您的控制台！"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1276
msgid "Please read the following information before upgrading."
msgstr "请在升级之前阅读以下信息。"

# type: <p><list>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1316
msgid ""
"The console device will change from <file>ttyS0</file> to <file>ttyS1</"
"file>, <file>ttyS2</file>, or <file>ttyS3</file> so"
msgstr "因为控制台设备将会由 <file>ttyS0</file> 变成 <file>ttyS1</"
"file>，<file>ttyS2</file> 或 <file>ttyS3</file>，所以"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"Edit <file>/etc/inittab</file> to add a getty entry for <file>/dev/ttyS1</"
"file> (rx4640, rx5670, rx7620, rx8620, Superdome), <file>/dev/ttyS2</file> "
"(rx1600), or <file>/dev/ttyS3</file> (rx2600)."
msgstr "请编辑 <file>/etc/inittab</file> 并替 <file>/dev/ttyS1</"
"file> (rx4640, rx5670, rx7620, rx8620, Superdome)，<file>/dev/ttyS2</file> "
"(rx1600) 或 <file>/dev/ttyS3</file> (rx2600) 新增一个项目。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"Edit <file>/etc/securetty</file> to add <file>ttyS1</file>, <file>ttyS2</"
"file>, or <file>ttyS3</file>."
msgstr "编辑 <file>/etc/securetty</file> 以新增 <file>ttyS1</file>，<file>ttyS2</"
"file> 或 <file>ttyS3</file>。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"Leave the existing <file>ttyS0</file> entries in <file>/etc/inittab</file> "
"and <file>/etc/securetty</file> so you can still boot old kernels."
msgstr "保留在 <file>/etc/inittab</file> 中原有的 <file>ttyS0</file> 及 <file>/etc/securetty</file> 这样您才可以继续以旧的内核开机。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid "Edit <file>/etc/elilo.conf</file> to remove any \"console=\" arguments."
msgstr "编辑 <file>/etc/elilo.conf</file> 并移除所有的 \"console=\" 参数。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"Run <prgn>elilo</prgn> to install the bootloader with new configuration."
msgstr "执行 <prgn>elilo</prgn> 来以新的设置安装开机程序。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"Reboot and use the EFI boot option maintenance menu to select exactly one "
"device for console output, input, and standard error. Then do a cold reset "
"so the changes take effect."
msgstr "重新开机并使用 EFI 开机选项管理菜单来选择控制台输出、输入及标准错误的正确设备。"
"然后进行冷启动让这些设置生效。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"For the MP console, be careful to select the device with \"Acpi(HWP0002,700)/"
"Pci(...)/Uart\" in the path."
msgstr "针对 MP 的控制台，请小心得在目录中选定 \"Acpi(HWP0002,700)/"
"Pci(...)/Uart\" 设备。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"More details about these changes and troubleshooting hints are available at "
"<url id=\"http://lists.debian.org/debian-ia64/2005/01/msg00008.html\">."
msgstr "有关于这些改变及疑难排解技巧的更多详尽信息可于 <url id=\"http://lists.debian.org/debian-ia64/2005/01/msg00008.html\"> 取得。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid "Upgrading the kernel"
msgstr "进行内核的升级"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1319
msgid ""
"When you dist-upgrade from &oldreleasename; to &releasename;, it is strongly "
"recommended that you install a new linux-image-2.6-* metapackage. This "
"package may be installed automatically by the dist-upgrade process. You can "
"verify this by running:"
msgstr "当您由 &oldreleasename; 完整升级至 &releasename; 后，强烈建议您安装某个 linux-image-2.6-* 虚拟软件包。"
"这个软件包可能会在完整升级的过程中被自动安装。若想确认，请执行："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1361
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg -l | grep '^ii  linux-image'"
msgstr "# dpkg -l | grep '^ii  linux-image'"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1361
msgid ""
"If you do not see any output, then you will need to install a new linux-"
"image package by hand. To see a list of available linux-image-2.6 "
"metapackages, run:"
msgstr "如果您没有看到任何输出文字，那么您将得手动安装一个新的 linux-"
"image 虚拟软件包。"
"若想得到可用的 linux-image-2.6 虚拟软件包列表，请执行："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1368
#, no-wrap
msgid "# apt-cache search linux-image-2.6- | grep -v transition"
msgstr "# apt-cache search linux-image-2.6- | grep -v transition"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1368
msgid ""
"If you are unsure about which package to select, run <tt>uname -r</tt> and "
"look for a package with a similar name. For example, if you see '2.4.27-3-"
"686', it is recommended that you install <package>linux-image-2.6-686</"
"package>. You may also use <prgn>apt-cache</prgn> to see a long description "
"of each package in order to help choose the best one available. For example:"
msgstr "如果您无法确定该选择哪一个软件包，请执行 <tt>uname -r</tt> 并查看是否有名称类似的软件包。"
"比如说，如果您看到了  '2.4.27-3-"
"686'，在此建议您安装<package>linux-image-2.6-686</"
"package>。您也可以利用 <prgn>apt-cache</prgn> 来查看每个软件包的详细说明来让您能在其中选出最合适的软件包。"
"比如说："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1379
#, no-wrap
msgid "# apt-cache show linux-image-2.6-686"
msgstr "# apt-cache show linux-image-2.6-686"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1379
msgid ""
"You should then use <tt>aptitude install</tt> to install it. Once this new "
"kernel is installed you should reboot at the next available opportunity to "
"get the benefits provided by the new kernel version."
msgstr "接下来，您应该使用 <tt>aptitude install</tt> 来进行安装。当新的内核安装完毕"
"后，您应当找个适当时机重新开机，以便能享用新的内核版本所带来的种种好处。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1379
msgid ""
"For the more adventurous there is an easy way to compile your own custom "
"kernel on &debian;. Install the <package>kernel-package</package> tool and "
"read the documentation in <file>/usr/share/doc/kernel-package</file>."
msgstr "对于那些比较富有冒险心的人，我们也提供了一个在 &debian; 上自行编译内核 的"
"简易方法。请安装 <package>kernel-package</package> 工具并详细阅读在 <file>/"
"usr/share/doc/kernel-package</file> 里的说明文件。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1379
msgid "Things to do before rebooting"
msgstr "在重新开机前应该完成的工作"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1379
msgid ""
"When <tt>aptitude dist-upgrade</tt> has finished, the \"formal\" upgrade is "
"complete, but there are some other things that should be taken care of "
"<em>before</em> the next reboot."
msgstr "当 <tt>aptitude dist-upgrade</tt> 执行完毕后，系统升级“形式上”已经完成了，"
"但仍然有一些工作是在您下次重新启动系统<em>之前</em>应该要加以注意的。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1379
msgid "Rerun lilo"
msgstr "重新执行 lilo"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1379
msgid ""
"If you are using <package>lilo</package> as your bootloader (it is the "
"default bootloader for &oldreleasename;) it is strongly recommended that you "
"rerun lilo after the upgrade:"
msgstr "如果您还是使用 <package>lilo</package> 做为您的开机程序（它是 &oldreleasename 默认的开机程序），"
"在此强烈建议您在升级完毕后重新执行 lilo："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1406
#, no-wrap
msgid "# /sbin/lilo"
msgstr "# /sbin/lilo"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1406
msgid ""
"Notice this is needed even if you did not upgrade your system's kernel, as "
"lilo's second stage will change due to the package upgrade."
msgstr "请注意到，如果您并没有升级您的系统的内核，这个动作还是必要的，"
"因为 lilo 的第二阶段可能会因为软件包的升级而改变了。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1406
msgid ""
"Also, review the contents of your <file>/etc/kernel-img.conf</file> and make "
"sure that you have <em>do_bootloader = Yes</em> in it. That way the "
"bootloader will always be rerun after a kernel upgrade."
msgstr "同时，再次查看您的 <file>/etc/kernel-img.conf</file> 内容并确认其中有着 <em>do_bootloader = Yes</em>。"
"那么，在内核升级后就会必定会自动执行开机程序了。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1406
msgid ""
"If you encounter any issues when running <prgn>lilo</prgn> review the "
"symbolic links in <file>/</file> to <file>vmlinuz</file> and <file>initrd</"
"file>, as well as the contents of your <file>/etc/lilo.conf</file> for "
"discrepancies."
msgstr "如果您在执行 <prgn>lilo</prgn> 时遇到了任何问难，请再次检查在 <file>/</file> 里指向 <file>vmlinuz</file> 及 <file>initrd</"
"file> 的符号连结，以及您的 <file>/etc/lilo.conf</file> 的内容是否有什么不对劲的地方。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1433
msgid ""
"If you forgot to rerun <prgn>lilo</prgn> before the reboot or the system is "
"accidentally rebooted before you could do this manually, your system might "
"fail to boot. Instead of the lilo prompt, you will only see <em>LI</em> when "
"booting the system<footnote>For more information on <prgn>lilo</prgn>'s boot "
"error codes please see <url id=\"http://tldp.org/HOWTO/Bootdisk-HOWTO/a1483."
"html\" name=\"The Linux Bootdisk HOWTO\">.</footnote>. In order to recover "
"from this you will have to start up a media installation disk in <em>rescue</"
"em> mode. For more information on how to do this please review the <url id="
"\"http://wiki.debian.org/DebianInstaller/FAQ\" name=\"DebianInstaller FAQ\">."
msgstr "如果您在重新开机之前忘了执行 <prgn>lilo</prgn>，或者是在您有机会手动执行之前系统意外得重新开机了，"
"您的系统很可能会因而无法开机。在开机时，您将看不到 lilo 提示字符，取而代之的是 <em>LI</em>。"
"<footnote>有关 <prgn>lilo</prgn> 的开机错误信息之更详尽信息请参考 <url id=\"http://tldp.org/HOWTO/Bootdisk-HOWTO/a1483."
"html\" name=\"The Linux Bootdisk HOWTO\"></footnote>。"
"为了进行救援，您必须利用安装媒体开机并以 <em>rescue</"
"em> 模式启动。对于如何进行的更多详尽信息请参考 <url id="
"\"http://wiki.debian.org/DebianInstaller/FAQ\" name=\"Debian 安装程序 问题与解答\">。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1433
msgid "Upgrading mdadm"
msgstr "更新 mdadm"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1433
msgid ""
"mdadm now needs a configuration file to assemble MD arrays (RAID) from the "
"initial ramdisk and during the system initialisation sequence. Please make "
"sure to read and act upon the instructions in <file>/usr/share/doc/mdadm/"
"README.upgrading-2.5.3.gz</file> after the package has been upgraded "
"<strong>and before you reboot</strong>. The latest version of this file is "
"available at <url id=\"http://svn.debian.org/wsvn/pkg-mdadm/mdadm/trunk/"
"debian/README.upgrading-2.5.3?op=file\">; please consult it in case of "
"problems."
msgstr "mdadm 现在需要设置文件来在 initial ramdisk 及系统初始化过程中建构 MD 阵列。"
"在该软件包被更新后、<strong>在您重新启动之前</strong>，请务必阅读并依照 <file>/usr/share/doc/mdadm/"
"README.upgrading-2.5.3.gz</file> 的内容进行。"
"这个档案的最新版可以在 <url id=\"http://svn.debian.org/wsvn/pkg-mdadm/mdadm/trunk/"
"debian/README.upgrading-2.5.3?op=file\"> 取得，若遭遇任何问题请不妨参阅。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1433
msgid "Obsolete packages"
msgstr "被废弃的软件包"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1457
msgid ""
"Introducing several thousand new packages, &releasename; also retires and "
"omits more than two thousand old packages that were in &oldreleasename;. It "
"provides no upgrade path for these obsolete packages. While nothing prevents "
"you from continuing to use an obsolete package where desired, the Debian "
"project will usually discontinue security support for it a year after "
"&releasename;'s release<footnote>Or for as long as there is not another "
"release in that time frame. Typically only two stable releases are supported "
"at any given time.</footnote>, and will not normally provide other support "
"in the meantime. Replacing them with available alternatives, if any, is "
"recommended."
msgstr "虽然在 &releasename; 里采用了数千个新的软件包，但它同时也撤除并舍弃了超过两千个"
"曾经包含在 &oldreleasename; 里的旧软件包。它将不会再提供这些已遭废弃的软件包任何"
"的升级途径，虽然我们并不会禁止您企图继续使用这些已遭废弃的软件包，但依惯例，在 "
"&releasename; 发布的一年之后 Debian 专案将不会再针对它们继续提供安全上的支持"
"<footnote>或是直到在这段期间内有新的发行版推出为止。基本上，我们只会同时维护"
"两个 stable 的发行版。</footnote>，而除此之外，我们在这段期间内一般并不会再"
"提供其它方面的支持。如果可以的话，我们建议您能采用其它的替代方案来取代这些软件"
"包。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1457
msgid ""
"There are many reasons why packages might have been removed from the "
"distribution: they are no longer maintained upstream; there is no longer a "
"Debian Developer interested in maintaining the packages; the functionality "
"they provide has been superseded by different software (or a new version); "
"or they are no longer considered suitable for &releasename; due to bugs in "
"them. In the later case, packages might still be present in the \"unstable\" "
"distribution."
msgstr "而这些软件包为什么会从发行版中移去的原因不一而足：有的是因为它的原始程序已经没"
"有人在继续维护了；有的是因为已经没有 Debian 的开发者有意愿想要继续维护这些套"
"件了；有的是因为它们所提供的功能已经被其它的软件（或是新的版本）所取代了；有"
"的是因为它们本身所包含的一些 Bug 使得我们认为它们已无法和 &releasename; 相"
"容。如果是最后一个情况，这些软件包很可能是被放在 \"unstable\" 这个分类里。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1457
msgid ""
"Detecting which packages in an updated system are \"obsolete\" is easy since "
"the package management front-ends will mark them as such. If you are using "
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn>, you will see a listing of these packages in the "
"\"Obsolete and Locally Created Packages\" entry. <prgn>dselect</prgn> "
"provides a similar section but the listing it presents might differ. Also, "
"if you have used <prgn>aptitude</prgn> to manually install packages in "
"&oldreleasename; it will have kept track of those packages you manually "
"installed and will be able to mark as obsolete those packages pulled in by "
"dependencies alone which are no longer needed if a package has been removed. "
"Also, <prgn>aptitude</prgn>, unlike <prgn>deborphan</prgn> will not mark as "
"obsolete packages that you manually installed, as opposed to those that were "
"automatically installed through dependencies."
msgstr "因为软件包管理的前端界面会将这些软件包标示为 \"废弃(obsolete)\"，因而我们可以很轻"
"易得就可以判断在一个已经过升级后的系统里，哪些软件包已遭废弃了。如果您所使用的"
"是 <prgn>aptitude</prgn>，您可以在【废弃及本机所建立的软件包, Obsolete and "
"Locally Created Packages】这个项目里看到这些软件包的列表。在 <prgn>dselect</"
"prgn> 里也提供了类似的功能但它所显示的列表可能会有点不太一样。同时，如果您之"
"前是手动使用 <prgn>aptitude</prgn> 来安装 &oldreleasename; 的软件包，它会持续得"
"跟踪这些您手动安装的软件包，并且如果有某个软件包被移除了，而使得这些因依赖关系而"
"被安装的软件包已经不再有任何作用时，它可以找出这些软件包并将其标示为 \"废弃\"。而"
"像是 <prgn>deborphan</prgn> 并不会将您手动安装的软件包标示为 \"废弃\"；但 "
"<prgn>aptitude</prgn> 则是完全相反，即使这些软件包是因为依赖性才被自动安装进来"
"的。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1457
msgid ""
"There are additional tools you can use to find obsolete packages such as "
"<prgn>deborphan</prgn>, <prgn>debfoster</prgn> or <prgn>cruft</prgn>. "
"<prgn>deborphan</prgn> is highly recommended, although it will (in default "
"mode) only report obsolete libraries: packages in the \"libs\" or \"oldlibs"
"\" sections that are not used by any other packages. Do not blindly remove "
"the packages these tools present, especially if you are using aggressive non-"
"default options that are prone to produce false positives. It is highly "
"recommended that you manually review the packages suggested for removal (i."
"e. their contents, size and description) before you remove them."
msgstr "还有一些其它的软件包可以让您用来寻找这些废弃了的软件包，像是 <prgn>deborphan</"
"prgn>、<prgn>debfoster</prgn> 或 <prgn>cruft</prgn>。其中推荐使用 "
"<prgn>deborphan</prgn>，因为它在默认的模式下只会报告已遭废弃了的函数库：位于 "
"\"libs\" 或 \"oldlibs\" 区的软件包就表示它们已不再被其它的软件包所使用了。但请不"
"要轻率得依据这些工具所回报的列表就把这些软件包给移掉了，尤其是您在执行时使用的"
"不是默认的，而是较为宽松的选项时，它们很可能会因而做出不正确的判定。因此在此"
"强烈建议您，在进行移除的动作之前，您必须亲自再重新检视一次这些将要被移除的套"
"件，包括它们的内容、大小，及它们的详细说明。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1514
msgid ""
"The <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name=\"Debian Bug Tracking System\"> often "
"provides additional information on why the package was removed. You should "
"review both the archived bug reports for the package itself and the archived "
"bug reports for the <url id=\"&url-bts;cgi-bin/pkgreport.cgi?pkg=ftp.debian."
"org&#38;archive=yes\" name=\"ftp.debian.org pseudo-package\">."
msgstr "在 <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name=\"Debian 错误跟踪系统\"> 里常常会提供了为什么某"
"个软件包会被移掉的相关信息。您可以使用该软件包本身的 bug report 数据库，或是在"
" <url id=\"&url-bts;cgi-bin/pkgreport.cgi?pkg=ftp.debian."
"org&#38;archive=yes\" name=\"ftp.debian.org pseudo-package\"> 里的 bug report 数据库来重新检视这些信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1514
msgid "Dummy packages"
msgstr "替代 (Dummy) 软件包"

# type: <p><p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1519
msgid ""
"Some packages from &oldreleasename; have been split into several packages in "
"&releasename;, often to improve system maintainability. To ease the upgrade "
"path in such cases, &releasename; often provides \"dummy\" packages: empty "
"packages that have the same name as the old package in &oldreleasename; with "
"dependencies that cause the new packages to be installed. These \"dummy\" "
"packages are considered obsolete packages after the upgrade and can be "
"safely removed."
msgstr "有时为了让系统能更易于管理，有些原来是包含于 &oldreleasename; 的软件包在 "
"&releasename; 里已被分开成数个软件包。在此况状下，为了能让升级的过程更加顺遂，"
"&releasename; 通常会采取提供 替代 (Dummy) 软件包的方式：使用一个和原本是包含于 "
"&oldreleasename; 的软件包相同名称的软件包，但它的内容却是空的，但利用依赖上的关联"
"性来使得新的软件包能被安装。这些替代软件包在升级之后就会被视同废弃软件包了，您可以"
"放心得移除它们。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1519
msgid ""
"Most (but not all) dummy packages' descriptions indicate their purpose. "
"Package descriptions for dummy packages are not uniform, however, so you "
"might also find <prgn>deborphan</prgn> with the <tt>--guess</tt> options "
"useful to detect them in your system. Note that some dummy packages are not "
"intended to be removed after an upgrade but are, instead, used to keep track "
"of the current available version of a program over time."
msgstr "大多数（但不是所有）的替代软件包会在软件包的说明中会介绍它们的用途，虽然它们的说"
"明的格式并不统一，所以您可能会发现 <prgn>deborphan</prgn> 在搭配 <tt>--"
"guess</tt> 选项时可以轻易得把它们从您的系统中找出来。请注意，有些替代软件包并不"
"希望您在升级后就将其删除，因为日后您可以替而使用它来跟踪是否有任何新版本出"
"现。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1545
msgid "Issues to be aware of for &releasename;"
msgstr "在 &releasename; 您必须知道的一些问题"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1545
msgid "Potential problems"
msgstr "潜在的问题"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1545
msgid ""
"Sometimes, changes have side-issues we cannot reasonably avoid, or we expose "
"bugs somewhere else. We document here the issues we are aware of. Please "
"also read the errata, the relevant packages' documentation, bug reports and "
"other information mentioned in <ref id=\"morereading\">."
msgstr "有时，更动会产生一些我们无法有效避免的次要问题，或者是会导致我们在其它地方遇到错误。"
"我们在此记述了一些我们所知道的问题。"
"请同时参阅勘误表、相关软件包之说明文件、错误回报及其它在 <ref id=\"morereading\"> 中所提及的信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1545
msgid "Certain networking site cannot be reached by TCP"
msgstr "有些网络站台无法用 TCP 连线。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1562
msgid ""
"Since 2.6.17, Linux aggresively uses TCP window scaling which is specified "
"in RFC 1323. Some servers have a broken behaviour, and announce wrong window "
"sizes for themselves. Please see the bugs <url id=\"http://bugs.debian."
"org/381262\" name=\"#381262\"> and <url id=\"http://bugs.debian.org/395066\" "
"name=\"#395066\"> for more information."
msgstr "从 2.6.17 开始，Linux 决定采用 RFC 1323 所说明的 TCP window scaling。"
"有些服务器对此适应不良，并会发送错误的 window 大小。"
"请参阅 <url id=\"http://bugs.debian."
"org/381262\" name=\"#381262\"> 及 <url id=\"http://bugs.debian.org/395066\" "
"name=\"#395066\"> 以取得更详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1562
msgid "Automatic poweroff stops working"
msgstr "自动关机无法正常运作"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1575
msgid ""
"On some older systems, <tt>shutdown -h</tt> may not power off the system "
"anymore (but just stop it). This happens because apm needs to be used there. "
"Adding <tt>acpi=off apm=power_off</tt> to the kernel's command line, e.g. in "
"<package>grub</package> or <package>lilo</package> configuration files "
"should fix this issue. Please see bug <url id=\"http://bugs.debian.org/390547"
"\" name=\"#390547\"> for additional information."
msgstr "在一些较为老旧的系统上，<tt>shutdown -h</tt> 将再也无法将系统关机了。（只能做到停止运作）。"
"这是因为在此必须使用 apm 才行。"
"请在像是 <package>grub</package> 或 <package>lilo</package> 的设置文件里，在内核的命令行上新增 <tt>acpi=off apm=power_off</tt> 应该就能解决这个问题。"
"请参阅 <url id=\"http://bugs.debian.org/390547"
"\" name=\"#390547\"> 以取得更多详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1575
msgid "Apt downloads small files with update"
msgstr "Apt 会在更新时下载小档案"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1582
msgid ""
"Support has been added to <prgn>apt</prgn> to download only the difference "
"between packages files. This is handy for people with bad network "
"connections, but people having a very nearby mirror may want to disable this "
"feature. One can disable it by adding <tt>Acquire::Pdiffs \"false\";</tt> to "
"<file>/etc/apt/apt.conf</file>."
msgstr "<prgn>apt</prgn> 新增了只会下载软件包之间的差异文件的功能。"
"这对于那些有着糟糕的网络环境的人们有极大的助益。"
"但有些有着速度不错的镜像站的人们可能想要关闭这个功能。"
"要关闭这个功能只要将 <tt>Acquire::Pdiffs \"false\";</tt> 加到 <file>/etc/apt/apt.conf</file> 里即可。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1582
msgid "ACPI support disabled for some HP laptop models in &releasename; kernel"
msgstr "在 &releasename; 的内核里，有些 HP 笔记型电脑机种的 ACPI 支持被关闭了"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1593
msgid ""
"Certain models of HP laptops have an ACPI BIOS that is incompatible with the "
"Linux 2.6.18 kernel shipped in &releasename;, which would prevent the fans "
"from spinning up leading to unnecessary heat stress. Also, fans might not "
"work after the system is suspedend. The kernel therefore disables ACPI "
"support internally when it detects certain ACPI BIOS versions. Models known "
"to be affected by this change include the HP nx6125, nx6120, nx6325, nc6120 "
"and nc6000 models."
msgstr "&releasename; 所搭载的 Linux 2.6.18内核和有些 HP 笔记型电脑机种里，用来防止风扇因旋转而导致的热压的 ACPI BIOS 不相容；"
"而同时，在系统待机后，风扇可能会不再运转。"
"因此，当内核探测到这些 ACPI BIOS 版本的话，会从内部将 ACPI 的支持关闭。"
"已知受此影响的包括了 HP nx6125、nx6120、nx6325、nc6120 "
"及 nc6000 机种。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1610
msgid ""
"Users who require ACPI support on these systems may install a Linux 2.6.19 "
"or later kernel. Please see Debian bug <url id=\"http://bugs.debian."
"org/404143\" name=\"#404143\"> and <url id=\"http://bugs.debian.org/400488\" "
"name=\"#400488\">, and Linux内核's bugs <url id=\"http://bugzilla.kernel."
"org/show_bug.cgi?id=5534\" name=\"#5534\"> and <url id=\"http://bugzilla."
"kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=7122\" name=\"#7122\"> for additional information."
msgstr "在这些系统上有需要用到 ACPI 支持的用户可以安装 Linux 2.6.19 或更新版的 kernel。"
"请参阅 Debian bug <url id=\"http://bugs.debian."
"org/404143\" name=\"#404143\"> 及 <url id=\"http://bugs.debian.org/400488\" "
"name=\"#400488\">，以及 Linux内核 的 bugs <url id=\"http://bugzilla.kernel."
"org/show_bug.cgi?id=5534\" name=\"#5534\"> 及 <url id=\"http://bugzilla."
"kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=7122\" name=\"#7122\"> 以取得更多详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1649
msgid "Upgrading to a 2.6 kernel"
msgstr "将内核升级至 2.6"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1649
msgid ""
"The 2.6 kernel series contains major changes from the 2.4 series. Modules "
"have been renamed and a lot of drivers have been partially or sometimes "
"almost completely rewritten. Upgrading to a 2.6 kernel from an earlier "
"version is therefore not a process to be undertaken lightly. This section "
"aims to make you aware of some of the issues you may face."
msgstr "和 2.4 系列的内核 相较，2.6 系列包含了很多重大的改变。像是模块的名称已经有"
"所不同， 有不少的驱动程序被局部甚至是完全改写。所以要把一些旧有版本的 "
"内核升级至 2.6 并不会是件容易事。这段章节的目的就是要让您知道一些您可能会"
"遇到的问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1649
msgid ""
"You are therefore strongly advised not to upgrade to a 2.6 kernel as part of "
"the upgrade from &oldreleasename; to &releasename;. Instead, you should "
"first make sure your system works correctly with either the old kernel or "
"with a 2.4 kernel from &releasename; and do the upgrade to a 2.6 kernel "
"later as a separate project."
msgstr "所以，在此强烈建议您不要把升级至 2.6内核 做为将 &oldreleasename; 升级至 "
"&releasename; 的计划的一部份。您的首要工作应该是确认您的系统和旧的内核或"
"是 &releasename; 上的 2.4 系列的内核搭配时能够正常运作。而将内核升级"
"至 2.6 则应该视为个别的计划。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1649
msgid ""
"If you compile your own kernel from source, make sure you install "
"<package>module-init-tools</package> before you reboot with the 2.6 kernel. "
"This package replaces <package>modutils</package> for 2.6 kernels. If you "
"install one of the Debian <package>linux-image</package> packages, this "
"package will be installed automatically because of dependencies."
msgstr "如果您是自行由源码来编译内核 的，请在使用 2.6内核 来重新开机前确"
"认您已安装了 <package>module-init-tools</package>。这个软件包在 2.6 的内核 里是用来取"
"代 <package>modutils</package> 的。如果您安装了任何的 <package>linux-image</package> 软件包，这"
"个软件包会因依赖上的因素而被自动地安装上去。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1649
msgid ""
"If you use <em>LVM</em>, you should also install <package>lvm2</package> "
"before you reboot as the 2.6 kernel does not directly support LVM1. To "
"access LVM1 volumes, the compatibility layer of <package>lvm2</package> (the "
"dm-mod module) is used. You can leave <package>lvm10</package> installed; "
"the init scripts will detect which kernel is used and execute the "
"appropriate version."
msgstr "如果您使用了 <em>LVM</em>，请在重新开机前确认您已安装了 <package>lvm2</package>，因为 2.6 "
"的内核 并不直接支持 LVM1，而是使用相容的 <package>lvm2</package>（dm-mod 模块）来存"
"取 LVM1 的 volumes。您还是可以保留已安装了的 <package>lvm10</package>；而进行初始化的 "
"Script 将会进行探测并依所使用的内核 的不同而自动载入适当的版本。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1649
msgid ""
"If you have entries in the <file>/etc/modules</file> file (the list of "
"modules to be loaded during system boot), be aware that some module names "
"may have changed. If this happens you will have to update this file with the "
"new module names."
msgstr "如果您在 <file>/etc/modules</file> 文件（在系统开机时所要载入的模块列表）有自"
"行加入的项目的话，请您要记得有些模块的名称已经有所改变，如果真的如此，您必须"
"修改这个文件并使用新的模块名称。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1685
msgid ""
"For some SATA disk controllers, the device assigned to a drive and its "
"partitions may change from <file>/dev/hdX</file> to <file>/dev/sdX</file>. "
"If this happens, you will have to modify your <file>/etc/fstab</file> and "
"bootloader configuration accordingly. Unless these changes are made "
"correctly, your system may not boot correctly<footnote>It will boot the "
"kernel but will fail when trying to mount the root filesystem and will abort "
"with an error <em>waiting for root filesystem</em> followed by <em>unable to "
"mount /dev/hdX ..not found</em>. You can use the <prgn>initramfs</prgn> "
"shell to fix this issue, after you identify the names newly assigned devices "
"in the kernel boot messages or by reviewing the contents of <file>/dev/disk</"
"file>.</footnote>."
msgstr "在一些 SATA 硬盘控制器里，将指派给硬盘及其分区的设备由 <file>/dev/hdX</file> 改变为 <file>/dev/sdX</file>。如果真的如此，您必须适当得修改您的 "
"<file>/etc/fstab</file> 及开机程序的设置。"
"在这些变更被正确得修改之前，您的系统可能会无法正常开机。"
"<footnote>它将能够启动内核但是会在试着挂载 root 文件系统时失败，且将会跳出并留下如下错误 <em>waiting for root filesystem</em> 以及 <em>unable to "
"mount /dev/hdX ..not found</em>。"
"您可以利用内核开机信息确认指派给设备的新名称或是重新查看<file>/dev/disk</"
"file>，然后使用 <prgn>initramfs</prgn> 的 Shell 来修正这个问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1685
msgid ""
"Once you have installed your 2.6 kernel, but before you reboot, make sure "
"you have a recovery method. First, make sure that the bootloader "
"configuration has entries for both the new kernel and the old, working 2.4 "
"kernel. You should also ensure you have a \"rescue\" floppy or cdrom to "
"hand, in case misconfiguration of the bootloader prevents you booting the "
"old kernel."
msgstr "如果您安装好了您的 2.6内核，请在重新开机之前，确认您已准备好紧急回复方案。"
"首先，请确认在您的开机程序的设置档里包含着您新的内核 以及旧的、可正常作业"
"的 2.4内核 的项目。您应该也要确认在您的手边有着 \"救援 (rescue)\" 硬盘片或"
"光盘，以防止在开机程序的一些错误设置导致您连旧的内核都无法开机。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1709
msgid "Keyboard configuration"
msgstr "键盘的设置"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1709
msgid ""
"The most invasive change in the 2.6 kernels is a fundamental change of the "
"input layer. This change makes all keyboards look like \"normal\" PC "
"keyboards. This means that if you currently have a different type of "
"keyboard selected (e.g. a USB-MAC or Sun keyboard), you will very likely end "
"up with a non-working keyboard after rebooting with the new 2.6 kernel."
msgstr "在 2.6内核 里最具冲击性的改变就是发生在输入层的根本改变。这个改变将会使得"
"所有的键盘都会看起来像是 \"一般\" 的 PC 键盘。也就是说，如果您正在使用的键盘"
"和一般的有所不同的话，（例： USB-MAC 或 Sun 键盘），在使用新的 2.6 的内核 "
"重新开机后，您的键盘很可能会无法正常运作。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1709
msgid ""
"If you can SSH into the box from another system, you can resolve this issue "
"by running <tt>dpkg-reconfigure console-data</tt>, choosing the option "
"\"Select keymap from full list\" and selecting a \"pc\" keyboard."
msgstr "如果您可以从另一个系统来使用 SSH 连进去那台主机，您可以执行 <tt>dpkg-"
"reconfigure console-data</tt>，并选择【Select keymap from full list】设置，"
"然后选择【pc】键盘来解决这个问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1709
msgid ""
"If your console keyboard is affected, you will probably also need to "
"reconfigure your keyboard for the X Window System. You can do this either by "
"running <tt>dpkg-reconfigure xserver-xorg</tt> or by editing <file>/etc/X11/"
"xorg.conf</file> directly. Don't forget to read the documentation referred "
"to in <ref id=\"nownownow\">."
msgstr "如果您在 Consle 所使用的键盘受到了影响，那么您大概也需要替 X Window System 重"
"新设置键盘。您可以执行 <tt>dpkg-reconfigure xerver-xorg</tt> 或是直接编"
"辑 <file>/etc/X11/"
"xorg.conf</file> 来达到这个目的。请不要忘了要阅读在 "
"<ref id=\"nownownow\"> 里所提到的文件。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1709
msgid ""
"This issue is unlikely to affect the &arch-title; architecture as all PS/2 "
"and most USB keyboards will already be configured as a \"normal\" PC "
"keyboard."
msgstr "这个问题似乎不会影响到 &arch-title; 结构的机器，因为所有的 PS/2 及绝大多数的 "
"USB 键盘应该早已设置为 \"一般的\" PC 键盘了。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1709
msgid ""
"Note that if you are using a USB keyboard, this may be configured as either "
"a \"normal\" PC keyboard or as a USB-MAC keyboard. In the first case you "
"will not be affected by this issue."
msgstr "请注意，如果您正在使用的是 USB 键盘，它可能会被设置为 \"一般的\" PC 键盘或是"
"设置为 USB-MAC 键盘。如果是前者的话，您将不会受到这个问题的影响。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1743
msgid "Mouse configuration"
msgstr "鼠标的设置"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1743
msgid ""
"Again because of the changes in the input layer, you may have to reconfigure "
"the X Window System and <package>gpm</package> if your mouse is not working "
"after upgrading to a 2.6 kernel. The most likely cause is that the device "
"which gets the data from the mouse has changed. You may also need to load "
"different modules."
msgstr "再一次地，因为输入层的改变，如果您在升级至 2.6 的内核后鼠标无法正常运作的"
"话，您也许得要重新设置 X Window System 及 <package>gpm</package> 才行。这大多是因为负"
"责读取鼠标资料的设备已经改变了，您也许还得载入其它额外的模块。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1743
msgid ""
"If you currently have X configured for <file>/dev/sunmouse</file>, you "
"probably need to change this to <file>/dev/psaux</file>."
msgstr "如果您目前已将 X 设为使用 <file>/dev/sunmouse</file>，您也许得将其修正为 "
"<file>/dev/psaux</file>。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1759
msgid "Sound configuration"
msgstr "设置声音"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1759
msgid ""
"For the 2.6 kernel series the ALSA sound drivers are recommended over the "
"older OSS sound drivers. ALSA sound drivers are provided as modules by "
"default. In order for sound to work, the ALSA modules appropriate for your "
"sound hardware need to be loaded. In general this will happen automatically "
"if you have, in addition to the <package>alsa-base</package> package, either "
"the <package>hotplug</package> package or the <package>discover</package> "
"package installed. The <package>alsa-base</package> package also \"blacklists"
"\" OSS modules to prevent <prgn>hotplug</prgn> and <prgn>discover</prgn> "
"from loading them. If you have OSS modules listed in <file>/etc/modules</"
"file>, you should remove them."
msgstr "在 2.6 系列的内核 里，比起使用旧式的 OSS 音效驱动程序，使用 ALSA 的音效驱动程序"
"将会是个更佳选择。"
"在默认上是以模块的方式提供 ALSA 音效驱动程序。为了让音效正确运作，必须为您的音效硬件载入适切的 ALSA 模块。"
"如果您额外安装了 <package>alsa-base</package> 软件包、<package>hotplug</package> 软件包或是 <package>discover</package> 软件包，"
"那么适切的 ALSA 模块会被自动载入。<package>alsa-base</package> 软件包同时也会将 OSS 模块\"列入黑名单\" 以防止它们被 <prgn>hotplug</prgn> 及 <prgn>discover</prgn> 载入。"
"如果您在 <file>/etc/modules</"
"file> 中有加入 OSS 模块，您应该将它们移除。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid "Switching to 2.6 may activate udev"
msgstr "转换到 2.6 后可能会启用 udev"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid ""
"<package>udev</package> is a userspace implementation of devfs. It is "
"mounted over the <file>/dev</file> directory and will populate that "
"directory with devices supported by the kernel. It will also dynamically add "
"and remove devices as kernel modules are loaded or unloaded respectively, "
"working together with <package>hotplug</package> to detect new devices. "
"<package>udev</package> works only with 2.6 kernels."
msgstr "<package>udev</package> 是一个 devfs 在用户层级的实作。它挂载在 <file>/dev/</file> "
"目录下并能针对那些被内核所支持的设备进行即时的目录配置。它是借由和 "
"<package>hotplug</package> 搭配合作的方式来探测新的设备，并能够在移除或载入内核 的"
"模块的同时，动态得新增或移除相对应的设备。<package>udev</package> 仅能和 2.6 的 "
"内核搭配运作。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid ""
"As <package>udev</package> is automatically installed as a dependency of the "
"new default initrd generator used with the 2.6 kernels (<package>initramfs-"
"tools</package>), upgrading to a 2.6 kernel will normally result in "
"<package>udev</package> being activated. You can avoid installing "
"<package>udev</package> if you install an alternate initrd generator, such "
"as <package>yaird</package>. <package>initramfs-tools</package> is the "
"recommended initrd generator."
msgstr "因为 <package>udev</package> 将会因为和 2.6内核 搭配使用的新 initrd 产生程序 (<package>initramfs-"
"tools</package>) 有着依赖性而被自动安装。"
"升级至 2.6 内核一般会启用 <package>udev</package>。"
"如果您安装了其它的 initrd 产生程序，像是 <package>yaird</package>，您可以避免安装 <package>udev</package>。"
"但在此建议使用 <package>initramfs-tools</package> 做为 initrd 的产生程序。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid ""
"Although <package>udev</package> has been tested extensively, you may "
"experience minor problems with some devices that will need to be fixed. The "
"most common problems are changed permission and/or ownership of a device. In "
"some cases a device may not be created by default (e.g. <file>/dev/video</"
"file> and <file>/dev/radio</file>)."
msgstr "虽然 <package>udev</package> 已经过了广泛的测试，但您还是可能在某些设备上遇到一些必须"
"加以修正的小问题。最常见的问题是某个设备的权限及/或所有权上的变更。在某些状况"
"下，有些设备默认是不会被建立的。（如：<file>/dev/video</file> 和 <file>/"
"dev/radio</file>）。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid ""
"<package>udev</package> provides configuration mechanisms to deal with these "
"issues. See <manref section=\"8\" name=\"udev\"> and <file>/etc/udev</file> "
"for further information."
msgstr "<package>udev</package> 提供了配置方案以便您能处理这些问题。请查看 <manref name=\"udev"
"\" section=\"8\"> 和 <file>/etc/udev</file> 以取得更详尽的信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid "XFree86 to X.Org transition"
msgstr "将 XFree86 转换至 X.Org"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid ""
"The transition to X.Org involves some structural changes. In case all "
"installed packages are from Debian and also included in &releasename;, the "
"upgrade should work without problems. Experience has however shown there are "
"a few changes to be aware of as they can potentially cause issues during the "
"upgrade."
msgstr "转换至 X.Org 将会连带得产生一些结构上的改变。"
"如果所有安装的软件包都来自 Debian 且都存在于 &releasename;，那么升级将不会发生什么问题。"
"在此所列出的是在实地测试时，一些应该要知道的改变，因为它们可能会在升级的过程中发生潜在的问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid ""
"The most important change is that <file>/usr/X11R6/bin</file> has been "
"dropped and only remains as a symlink to <file>/usr/bin</file>. This means "
"this directory has to be empty at the time the new packages are installed. "
"The new packages conflict with most packages that used <file>/usr/X11R6/bin</"
"file>, but in some cases manual intervention may be needed. Please remember "
"to not run upgrades within an X session."
msgstr "最重大的改变是 <file>/usr/X11R6/bin</file> 已被废止，只剩下一个符号连结指向 <file>/usr/bin</file>。"
"这表示这个目录必须在新软件包安装后清空。"
"这个新软件包将会和大多数使用 <file>/usr/X11R6/bin</"
"file> 的软件包发生冲突。在某些状况之下，也许需要手动介入。"
"请牢记切勿在 X session 里进行升级。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1779
msgid ""
"In case the upgrade aborts during X.Org installation, you should check if "
"any files are still left in <file>/usr/X11R6/bin</file>. You can then use "
"<tt>dpkg -S</tt> to find out which Debian package installed that file (if "
"any), and remove such packages with <tt>dpkg --remove</tt>. Please make a "
"note which packages you remove, so that you can install substitute packages "
"later on. Before continuing with the upgrade, all files in <file>/usr/X11R6/"
"bin</file> need to be removed."
msgstr "万一在安装 X.Org 时升级作业中断了，您应该检查是否还有什么文件还遗留在 <file>/usr/X11R6/bin</file> 里。"
"您可以使用 <tt>dpkg -S</tt> 来找到是哪些 Debian 软件包安装了那些文件（如果有的话），"
"然后用 <tt>dpkg --remove</tt> 来移除这些软件包。"
"请记下您移除了哪些软件包，那么您可以在稍后再安装其它的替代软件包。"
"在继续进行升级之前，在  <file>/usr/X11R6/"
"bin</file> 里的所有文件必须被清除掉。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1835
msgid ""
"Please read <url id=\"http://wiki.debian.org/Xorg69To7\"> for more details "
"and other issues."
msgstr "请参阅 <url id=\"http://wiki.debian.org/Xorg69To7\"> 以取得更多详尽信息及其它的问题。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1835
msgid "Upgrading from exim to exim4"
msgstr "将 exim 升级至 exim4"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1835
msgid ""
"One of the packages that has been obsoleted by the &releasename; release is "
"the Mail Transfer Agent (MTA) <package>exim</package>, which has been "
"replaced by the completely new package <package>exim4</package>."
msgstr "被 &releasename; 释出版本所废弃的软件包之一是 Mail Transfer Agent (MTA) <package>exim</package>，"
"它已完全被新的 <package>exim4</package> 软件包所取代。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1835
msgid ""
"<prgn>exim</prgn> (version 3.xx) has been unmaintained upstream for years, "
"and Debian has dropped support for that version as well. If you are still "
"using <prgn>exim</prgn> 3.xx, please upgrade your <package>exim</package> "
"installation to <package>exim4</package> manually. Since <package>exim4</"
"package> is already part of &oldreleasename;, you can choose to do the "
"upgrade on your &oldreleasename; system before the upgrade to &releasename;, "
"or after the &releasename; upgrade at your convenience. Just remember that "
"your old <package>exim</package> package is not going to be upgraded and "
"that it won't get security support after support for &oldreleasename; has "
"been discontinued."
msgstr "<prgn>exim</prgn>（3.xx 版）已有多年没有上游者在继续维护了，而同时 Debian 也中止了对这个版本的支持。"
"如果您还在用着 <prgn>exim</prgn> 3.xx，请手动将您的 <package>exim</package> 升级为 <package>exim4</package>。"
"因为 <package>exim4</"
"package> 已包含在 &oldreleasename; 之中，您可以自行选择是在升级至 &releasename; 之前或之后在您的 &oldreleasename; 系统上进行这项升级。"
"请牢记，您旧版的 <package>exim</package> 软件包将不会进行升级，且安全维护也将在 &oldreleasename; 的支持中止之后停止。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1835
msgid ""
"The <package>exim4</package> packages in Debian are extensively documented. "
"The package's home page is <url id=\"http://wiki.debian.org/PkgExim4\"> on "
"the Debian Wiki, and the README file can be found at <url id=\"http://pkg-"
"exim4.alioth.debian.org/README/README.Debian.html\"> and inside the packages "
"as well."
msgstr "在 Debian 里的 <package>exim4</package> 软件包已有众多的文件。"
"该软件包的首页为在 Debian Wiki 上的 <url id=\"http://wiki.debian.org/PkgExim4\">，"
"而 README 文件可以在 <url id=\"http://pkg-"
"exim4.alioth.debian.org/README/README.Debian.html\"> 及软件包中找到。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1835
msgid ""
"The README file has a chapter about Packaging, which explains the different "
"package variations we offer, and it has a chapter about Updating from "
"<prgn>Exim</prgn> 3, which will help you in doing the actual transition."
msgstr "在 README 文件中有个关于 Packaging 的章节，"
"说明了和我们所提供的软件包之间的一些差异，"
"它还有一个章节是从 <prgn>Exim</prgn> 3 升级的一些说明，这个将对于您在实地转换时有所帮助。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1864
msgid "Upgrading apache2"
msgstr "升级 apache2"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1864
msgid ""
"Apache has been upgraded to the new version 2.2. Although this shouldn't "
"impact the average user, there are some potential issues to be aware of."
msgstr "Apache 已被升级为新版的 2.2。"
"虽然对于一般用户而这并不是很重要，但还是有些潜在的问题必须知道。"

# type: <p><list>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1864
msgid ""
"<url id=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.2/upgrading.html\"> contains the "
"upstream changes. Please read this page, and remember that especially:"
msgstr "在 <url id=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.2/upgrading.html\"> 上包含了上游的改变，"
"请参阅这个网页，并请特别牢记："

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid "all modules need to be recompiled"
msgstr "所有的模块必须重新编译"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid "authorization modules have been resorted and renamed"
msgstr "认证模块已被重新排列并重新命名了"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid "some configuration options have been renamed"
msgstr "有些设置项目被更名了"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid ""
"Debian-specific changes include that the string SSL is no longer defined, as "
"ssl is now supported by the default package."
msgstr "而仅适于 Debian 的改变包括了 SSL 字符串已不再被定义了，"
"因为 ssl 现已被默认的软件包所支持"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid "Deprecated insecure php configurations"
msgstr "关闭不安全的 php 设置"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid ""
"For many years, turning on the <tt>register_globals</tt> settings in PHP has "
"been known to be insecure and dangerous, and this option has defaulted to "
"off for some time now. This configuration is now finally deprecated on "
"Debian systems as too dangerous. The same applies to flaws in <tt>safe_mode</"
"tt> and <tt>open_basedir</tt>, which have also been unmaintained for some "
"time."
msgstr "多年以来，在 PHP 里启用 <tt>register_globals</tt> 设置是众所皆知的既不安全且极为冒险的，"
"而这个选项也被多次在默认上被关闭。"
"这个设置终于因为太危险而在 Debian 系统里被关闭了。"
"同样的问题也发生在 <tt>safe_mode</"
"tt> 及 <tt>open_basedir</tt> 上，因为它们已有段时间没有在继续维护了。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid ""
"Starting with this release, the Debian security team does not provide "
"security support for a number of PHP configurations which are known to be "
"insecure. Most importantly, issues resulting from <tt>register_globals</tt> "
"being turned on will no longer be addressed."
msgstr "从这个释出版本开始，Debian 安全团队将不再替一些已知是不安全的 php 设置提供安全上的支持。"
"最重要的是，将不再关注于因为开启了 <tt>register_globals</tt> 而导致的问题。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid ""
"If you run legacy applications that require <tt>register_globals</tt>, "
"enable it for the respective paths only, e.g. through the Apache "
"configuration file. More information is available in the <file>README.Debian."
"security</file> file in the PHP documentation directory (<file>/usr/share/"
"doc/php4</file>, <file>/usr/share/doc/php5</file>)."
msgstr "如果您所运行的老旧应用程序需要使用 <tt>register_globals</tt>，"
"请在各别的页面中，像是在 Apache 的设置里将其启用。"
"可以在 PHP 文件目录(<file>/usr/share/"
"doc/php4</file>、<file>/usr/share/doc/php5</file>) 里的 <file>README.Debian."
"security</file> 里找到更多的详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid "Security status of Mozilla products"
msgstr "Mozilla 组合的安全状态"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1874
msgid ""
"The Mozilla programs are important tools for many users. Unfortunately the "
"upstream security policy is to urge users to update to new upstream "
"versions, which conflicts with Debian's policy not to ship large functional "
"changes in security updates. We cannot predict it today, but during lifetime "
"of &releasename; the Debian Security Team may come to a point where "
"supporting Mozilla products is no longer feasible and announce the end of "
"security support for Mozilla products. You should take this into account "
"when deploying Mozilla and consider alternatives available in Debian if the "
"absence of security support would pose a problem for you."
msgstr "Mozilla 程序对于很多用户而言是很重要的工具。"
"但很不幸的，它的上游的安全策略就是鼓励用户升级到新的版本。"
"这和 Debian 尽量不要在安全更新里提供太多功能上的变化的政策是相互扺触的。"
"我们无法在此预言，但在 &releasename; 存在的期间，Debian 安全团队有可能会走到再也无法继续维护 Mozilla 程序，"
"只好宣布中止对 Mozilla 程序的安全支持这一步。"
"您应该在布署 Mozilla 前先慎重考虑这个问题，如果没有安全支持对您会造成困扰的话，请考虑使用 Debian 的其它程序替代。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1920
msgid "KDE desktop"
msgstr "KDE 桌面"

# type: <p><p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1920
msgid ""
"KDE media handling has changed in the version available in &releasename; "
"from using <file>device:/</file> to <file>media:/</file>. Some user "
"configuration files might have stored <file>device:/</file> links in them "
"which should be adapted. Notably, <file>~/.kde/share/apps/konqsidebartng/"
"virtual_folders/services</file> contains this reference and can be safely "
"deleted as it will not be created when setting up new users."
msgstr "在 &releasename; 中所提供的 KDE 媒体管理程序因版本变更，已由使用 <file>device:/</file> 变为使用 <file>media:/</file>。"
"有些还在使用着 <file>device:/</file> 连结的用户设置必须更正。"
"请注意到，<file>~/.kde/share/apps/konqsidebartng/"
"virtual_folders/services</file> 包含了这项设置且可以安全得删除，让它不会在设置新的用户时被再次建立。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1933
msgid ""
"There have been many changes in the KDE desktop environment from the version "
"shipped in &oldreleasename; to the version in &releasename;, you can find "
"more information in the <url id=\"http://www.kde.org/announcements/announce-"
"3.5.php\" name=\"KDE 3.5 Release Notes\">."
msgstr "&oldreleasename; 所搭载的 KDE 桌面环境和 &releasename; 上的版本已有着许多不同，"
"您可以在 <url id=\"http://www.kde.org/announcements/announce-"
"3.5.php\" name=\"KDE 3.5 Release Notes\"> 上找到更多的详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1937
msgid "GNOME desktop changes and support"
msgstr "GNOME 桌面的变更和支持"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1937
msgid ""
"If you used the GNOME desktop in &oldreleasename; you will not benefit of "
"some of the changes introduced in the default configuration in Debian for "
"&releasename;. In some extreme cases the GNOME desktop might not properly "
"handle your old configuration and might not behave properly."
msgstr "如果您使用着 &oldreleasename; 所搭载的 GNOME 桌面环境，"
"您将无法在 Debian 里一些建议使用的默认设置的改变上得到助益。"
"在一些极端的例子里，GNOME 桌面环境可能无法正确得使用您旧有的设置，且可能无法适当得运作。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1937
msgid ""
"If you have not heavily invested in configuring your GNOME desktop you might "
"want to move the the <file>.gconf</file> directory in user's home "
"directories to a different name (such as <file>.gconf.old</file>) so that it "
"gets recreated, with the default configuration for &releasename;, upon "
"starting a new session."
msgstr "如果您对于您的 GNOME 桌面的设置不是很在乎的话，您可以把用户主目录里的 <file>.gconf</file> 目录更名，（像是 <file>.gconf.old</file>），"
"让它在启用新的连线时重新以 &releasename; 的默认设置重新产生。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1937
msgid ""
"With the release of &releasename;, Debian no longer contains packages for "
"most of the obsolete version 1 release of GNOME. Although some packages "
"remain in order to support some Debian packages which have not yet been "
"updated to GNOME 2. Packages for GTK1.2 remain fully maintained."
msgstr "在 &releasename; 释出版里， Debian 已不再包含大多数和 GNOME 已废弃的第 1 版的软件包。"
"虽然有些软件包被保留了下来，但也只为了要支持一些尚未升级到 GNOE 2 的 Debian 软件包。而 GTK1.2 软件包则还是被完整维护着。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1958
msgid ""
"There have been many changes in the GNOME desktop environment from the "
"version shipped in &oldreleasename; to the version in &releasename;, you can "
"find more information in the <url id=\"http://www.gnome.org/start/2.14/notes/"
"en/\" name=\"GNOME 2.14 Release Notes\">."
msgstr "&oldreleasename; 所搭载的 GNOME 桌面环境和 &releasename; 上的版本已有着许多不同，"
"您可以在 <url id=\"http://www.gnome.org/start/2.14/notes/"
"en/\" name=\"GNOME 2.14 Release Notes\"> 上找到更多的详尽信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1958
msgid "Default editor changed to nano"
msgstr "将默认的编辑器变更为 nano"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1958
msgid ""
"The default editor for default installations in &releasename; is "
"<package>nano</package>. Previous Debian releases set the default editor for "
"all users to <package>vim</package>, in this release the default behaviour "
"has changed and users will get a more user-friendly editor."
msgstr "在 &releasename; 上默认会安装的编辑器为 <package>nano</package>。"
"之前 Debian 释出版是将所有用户的默认编辑器设置为 <package>vim</package>，"
"在这个释出版中默认的方式已有所改变且用户会拥有一个更易于操作的编辑器。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1958
msgid ""
"Users wishing to retain the previous behaviour can either define the "
"environment variable <em>EDITOR</em> by introducing the following lines in "
"their own profiles:"
msgstr "那些希望保留原有方式的用户可以指定 <em>EDITOR</em> 环境变数。请在他们的 profiles 中加入以下几行："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1972
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"EDITOR=vi\n"
"export EDITOR\n"
"alias editor=$EDITOR"
msgstr "EDITOR=vi\n"
"export EDITOR\n"
"alias editor=$EDITOR"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1972
msgid ""
"Administrators that wish to change the behaviour for all users will have to "
"update the alternatives system using:"
msgstr "而如果管理者希望改变所有用户的操作模式，可以更新偏好系统如下："

# type: <example></example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1982
#, no-wrap
msgid "# update-alternatives --config editor"
msgstr "# update-alternatives --config editor"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1991
msgid "More information on &debian;"
msgstr "更多关于 &debian; 的信息"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1991
msgid "Further reading"
msgstr "阅读更多信息"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1991
msgid ""
"Beyond these release notes and the installation guide, further documentation "
"on &debian; is available from the Debian Documentation Project (DDP), whose "
"goal is to create high quality documentation for Debian users and "
"developers. Documentation including the Debian Reference, Debian New "
"Maintainers Guide, and Debian FAQ are available, and many more. For full "
"details of the existing resources see the <url id=\"&url-ddp;\" name=\"DDP "
"website\">."
msgstr "除了发行注记和安装指南之外，Debian 文件计划 (DDP) 也提供了许多 &debian; 更进"
"一步的说明文件。Debian 文件计划的目标是替 Debian 的用户和开发者创作出高品质"
"的文件，其中包括了 Debian 参考手册、Debian 新维护者指南、以及 Debian 常见问答集，"
"以及其他更多的文件。如果您想了解关于这些资源的完整信息，请参考 <url id="
"\"&url-ddp;\" name=\"DDP 网站\">。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1991
msgid ""
"Documentation for individual packages is installed into <file>/usr/share/doc/"
"<var>package</var></file>, this may include copyright information, Debian "
"specific details and any upstream documentation."
msgstr "个别软件包的说明文件则会被安装到 <file>/usr/share/doc/<var>package</var></"
"file> 目录之中，其中可能会包含了版权信息，专属于 Debian 的一些信息，以及任何"
"原作者所提供的说明文件。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1991
msgid "Getting help"
msgstr "获得帮助"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:1991
msgid ""
"There are many sources of help, advice and support for Debian users, but "
"these should only be considered if research into documentation of the issue "
"has exhausted all sources. This section provides a short introduction into "
"these which may be helpful for new Debian users."
msgstr "Debian 的用户可以从许多的管道取得协助、建议、和支持，但您应该只有在用尽了各"
"种手段却依然找不到问题的解答时才考虑寻求协助。这一节简单的介绍了对 Debian 的"
"新用户可能会很有帮助的求助管道。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2020
msgid "Mailing lists"
msgstr "邮件列表"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2020
msgid ""
"The mailing lists of most interest to Debian users are the debian-user list "
"(English) and other debian-user-<var>language</var> lists (for other "
"languages). For information on these lists and details of how to subscribe "
"see <url id=\"&url-debian-list-archives;\">. Please check the archives for "
"answers to your question prior to posting and also adhere to standard list "
"etiquette."
msgstr "Debian 的用户最感兴趣的邮件列表应该是 debian-user 论坛（英文）以及其他的 "
"debian-user-<var>language</var> 列表（其他语言）了。您可以在 <url id=\"&url-"
"debian-list-archives;\"> 取得这些列表的相关细节，以及订阅的方法。请您在列表中"
"发言前先检查过去的列表存档中是否已经提供了问题的解答，并请遵守邮件列表上的基"
"本礼节。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2030
msgid "Internet Relay Chat"
msgstr "IRC(Internet Relay Chat) 网络聊天室"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2030
msgid ""
"Debian has an IRC channel dedicated to the support and aid of Debian users "
"located on the OFTC IRC network which exists to provide interactive services "
"to peer-directed project communities. To access the channel, point your "
"favourite IRC client at &debian-irc-server; and join #debian."
msgstr "OFTC IRC 网络主要的目的就是向同仁导向的专案社群提供互动式的服务。在那"
"里 Debian 有一个 IRC 频道是专门用来支持并帮助 Debian 的用户的。您只要把您"
"惯用的 IRC 客户端程序指向 &opn-irc-server; 并加入 #debian 就可以连上这个频道"
"了。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2040
msgid ""
"Please follow the channel guidelines, respecting other users fully. For more "
"information on OFTC please visit the <url id=\"&url-irc-host;\" name="
"\"website\">."
msgstr "请遵循该频道的规定，并尊重在线的其他的用户。您可以在 <url id=\"&url-irc-host;\" name="
"\"website\"> 上取得更多 OFTC 的相关信息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2046
msgid "Reporting bugs"
msgstr "回报错误"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2046
msgid ""
"We strive to make Debian GNU/Linux a high quality operating system, however "
"that does not mean that the packages we provide are totally free of bugs. "
"Consistent with Debian's \"open development\" philosophy and as a service to "
"our users, we provide all the information on reported bugs at our own Bug "
"Tracking System (BTS). The BTS is browseable at <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name="
"\"bugs.debian.org\">."
msgstr "我们尽心尽力地让 Debian GNU/Linux 成为一个高品质的操作系统，但这并不表示我们"
"所提供的软件包都是完全没有任何问题的。为了和 Debian 一贯的开放发展原则相互呼"
"应，也为了能对我们的用户提供更好的服务，我们在我们自己的错误跟踪系统 (BTS) "
"中提供了对所有报告过的错误的所有信息。您可以在 <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name="
"\"bugs.debian.org\"> 浏览错误跟踪系统的网站。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2046
msgid ""
"If you find a bug in the distribution or in packaged software that is part "
"of it, please report it so that it can be properly fixed for next releases. "
"Reporting bugs requires a valid email address, we ask for this so that we "
"can trace bugs and developers can get in contact with submitters should they "
"need more information."
msgstr "如果您在我们的系统发行或其中的软件包中发现了任何问题，请向我们回报，这样我们才"
"能在下一次发行前将它修复。您需要拥有一个正确的电子邮件信箱才能够回报问题，会"
"有这个限制是因为这样我们才能藉此跟踪错误报告的进展，而当开发人员需要更多信息"
"的时候也才能和原问题报告者取得连系。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2046
msgid ""
"You can submit a bug report using the program <package>reportbug</package> "
"or manually using email. You can read more about the Bug Tracking System and "
"how to use it by reading the reference cards (available at <file>/usr/share/"
"doc/debian</file> if you have <package>doc-debian</package> installed) or "
"online at the <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name=\"Bug Tracking System\">."
msgstr "您可以借由 <package>reportbug</package> 程序或是自行使用电子邮件来进行回报错"
"误，您可以阅读参考卡片（如果您有安装 <package>doc-debian</package> 的话，可以"
"在 <file>/usr/share/doc/debian</file> 里找到）或到 <url id=\"&url-bts;\" "
"name=\"错误跟踪系统\"> 的在线网页取得更多如何使用错误跟踪系统及其它的相关信"
"息。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2074
msgid "Contributing to Debian"
msgstr "如何对 Debian 做贡献"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2088
msgid ""
"You do not need to be an expert to contribute to Debian. By assisting users "
"with problems on the various user support <url id=\"&url-debian-list-"
"archives;\" name=\"lists\"> you are contributing to the community. "
"Identifying (and importantly solving) problems related to the development of "
"the distribution by participating on the development <url id=\"&url-debian-"
"list-archives;\" name=\"lists\"> is also extremely helpful. To maintain "
"Debian's high quality distribution <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name=\"submit bugs"
"\"> and help developers track them down and fix them. If you have a way with "
"words then you may want to contribute more actively by helping to write <url "
"id=\"&url-ddp;\" name=\"documentation\"> or <url id=\"&url-debian-i18n;\" "
"name=\"translate\"> existing documentation into your own language."
msgstr "并不是只有个中高手才能对 Debian 做出贡献。当您在各个用户 <url id=\"&url-"
"debian-list-archives;\" name=\"邮件论坛\"> 中协助其他用户解决问题时，您就是"
"在对整个社群做出贡献。参与开发者 <url id=\"&url-debian-list-archives;\" name="
"\"邮件论坛\"> 以协助找出（更重要的是解决）和系统发行相关的问题对我们也有极大"
"的帮助。为了维护 Debian 系统发行一贯的高品质，请 <url id=\"&url-bts;\" name="
"\"报告问题\">，并协助开发人员找出问题的起因以修正错误。如果您有文字方面的天"
"份，您也可以选择借由 <url id=\"&url-ddp;\" name=\"文档\"> 的撰写或把现有的文"
"档 <url id=\"&url-debian-i18n;\" name=\"翻译\"> 成您所使用的语言来做出更直接"
"的贡献。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2099
msgid ""
"If you can dedicate more time, you could manage a piece of the Free Software "
"collection within Debian. Especially helpful is if people adopt or maintain "
"items that people have requested for inclusion within Debian, the <url id="
"\"&url-wnpp;\" name=\"Work Needing and Prospective Packages database\"> "
"details this information. If you have an interest in specific groups then "
"you may find enjoyment in contributing to some of Debian's subprojects which "
"include ports to particular architectures, <url id=\"&url-debian-jr;\" name="
"\"Debian Jr.\"> and <url id=\"&url-debian-med;\" name=\"Debian Med\">."
msgstr "如果您能投注更多的时间的话，您可以负责维护 Debian 中一部分的自由软件。如果您"
"能够接续或维护其他用户希望 Debian 所能提供的软件的话就更好了，您可以在 "
"<url id=\"&url-wnpp;\" name=\"亟需人手以及受到期待的软件包数据库 (WNPP)\"> 中取"
"得相关的信息。如果您的兴趣是集中在特别的领域之中，那您可能会想要参加像是某个"
"特定硬件平台的系统移植、<url id=\"&url-debian-jr;\" name=\"小小 Debian\">，以"
"及 <url id=\"&url-debian-med;\" name=\"Debian Med\"> 之类在 Debian 中的子计"
"划。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2099
msgid ""
"In any case, if you are working in the free software community in any way, "
"as a user, programmer, writer or translator you are already helping the free "
"software effort. Contributing is rewarding and fun, and as well as allowing "
"you to meet new people it gives you that warm fuzzy feeling inside."
msgstr "不论如何，只要您以任何的方式参加了自由软件社群的活动，不管是身为用户、程序"
"员、作者、还是译者，您就已经对自由软件的群体努力做出贡献了。贡献本身就是一件"
"非常有益而有趣的事情，除了能让您不断地遇见新的伙伴之外，也能让您的心中充满了"
"温暖的感觉。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2111
msgid "Managing your &oldreleasename; system"
msgstr "管理您的 &oldreleasename; 系统"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2111
msgid ""
"This appendix contains information on how to make sure you can install or "
"upgrade &oldreleasename; packages before you upgrade to &releasename;. This "
"should only be necessary in specific situations."
msgstr "这个附录包含了在您升级至 &releasename; 之前，如何让您能够顺利地安装或更新 "
"&oldreleasename; 软件包的相关说明。这只有在某些特殊状况之下才会有这个需求。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2118
msgid "Upgrading your &oldreleasename; system"
msgstr "更新您的 &oldreleasename; 系统"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2118
msgid ""
"Basically this is no different than any other upgrade of &oldreleasename; "
"you've been doing. The only difference is that you first need to make sure "
"your package list still contains &oldreleasename; packages as explained in "
"<ref id=\"old-sources\">."
msgstr "基本上，这和您所进行过的 &oldreleasename; 的升级并没有什么不同。唯一的不同是"
"您必须先确认您的软件包列表是否还是包含了 &oldreleasename; 的软件包，请参考在 "
"<ref id=\"old-sources\"> 里的说明。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2118
msgid ""
"You should upgrade to the latest &oldreleasename; point release: r5, "
"published February 2007."
msgstr ""
"您至少应该升级至最新的 &oldreleasename; 释出版本：r5，"
"于 2007 二月发布。"

# type: <heading></heading>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2131
msgid "Checking your sources list"
msgstr "检查您的来源列表"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2131
msgid ""
"If any of the lines in your <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> refer to "
"'stable', you are effectively already \"using\" &releasename;. If you have "
"already run <tt>apt-get update</tt>, you can still get back without problems "
"following the procedure below."
msgstr "如果在您的 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> 中有任何的项目是参照至 "
"'stable' 的话，您可能在实际上已经在 \"使用\" &releasename; 了。如果您已执行"
"了 <tt>apt-get update</tt> 的话，您还是可以轻易得回到原始的状态，只要您遵照以"
"下的指示即可。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2131
msgid ""
"If you have also already installed packages from &releasename;, there "
"probably is not much point in installing packages from &oldreleasename; "
"anymore. In that case you will have to decide for yourself whether you want "
"to continue or not. It is possible to downgrade packages, but that is not "
"covered here."
msgstr "如果您已经安装了来自 &releasename; 的软件包，那么再安装来自 &oldreleasename; 的"
"软件包就已经没有太多意义了。在此状况之下，您应该要自行决定是否要继续进行。进行"
"软件包的降级并不是不可能的事，但是在此并没有针对这个加以说明。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2131
msgid ""
"Open the file <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> with your favorite editor "
"(as root) and check all lines beginning with <tt>deb http:</tt> or <tt>deb "
"ftp:</tt> for a reference to \"<tt>stable</tt>\". If you find any, change "
"<tt>stable</tt> to <tt>&oldreleasename;</tt>."
msgstr "使用您惯用的编辑器，以 root 的身份开启 <file>/etc/apt/sources.list</file> 这"
"个文件，然后检查所有以 <tt>deb http:</tt> 或 <tt>deb ftp:</tt> 开头的项目，看"
"看是否有参照至 \"<tt>stable</tt>\"。如果有的话，将其中的 <tt>stable</tt> 改为 <tt>&oldreleasename;</tt>。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2131
msgid ""
"If you have any lines starting with <tt>deb file:</tt>, you will have to "
"check for yourself if the location they refer to contains a &oldreleasename; "
"or a &releasename; archive."
msgstr "如果您有任何项目是以 <tt>deb file:</tt> 开头的，您必须自行检查这些项目所提供"
"的是 &oldreleasename; 还是 &releasename; 的存档。"

# type: <p></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2131
msgid ""
"<strong>Important!</strong> Do not change any lines that begin with <tt>deb "
"cdrom:</tt>. Doing so would invalidate the line and you would have to run "
"<prgn>apt-cdrom</prgn> again. Do not be alarmed if a 'cdrom' source line "
"refers to \"<tt>unstable</tt>\". Although confusing, this is normal."
msgstr "<strong>极重要！</strong> 不要修改任何以 <tt>deb cdrom:</tt> 开头的项目。否则，这些项"
"目将会因而无法使用，使得您只能再执行一次 <prgn>apt-cdrom</prgn>。如果您发现某个 "
"'cdrom' 的来源项目是指向 \"<tt>unstable</tt>\" 时请不要觉得太讶异。虽然有点奇怪，"
"但这却是很正常的。"

# type: <p><example>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2131
msgid "If you've made any changes, save the file and execute"
msgstr "如果您进行了任何改变，将文件保存并执行"

# type: </example></p>
#: ../en/release-notes.en.sgml:2161
msgid "to refresh the package list."
msgstr "来更新软件包的列表。"

